{"type":"message","id":"096c550d","parentId":"5c5fb632","timestamp":"2026-06-28T10:46:19.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **Create a unified modal component** in `index.html` that:\n   - Shows a page-level overlay (not browser confirm/alert)\n   - Cannot be closed by clicking background\n   - Only closes via ESC or Cancel button\n   - Blocks background interaction\n\n2. **Replace all existing modals** with the unified component:\n   - `showAlert` → use `showModal`\n   - `showConfirm` → use `showModal`\n   - `quickAddModal` → use `showModal`\n   - `confirmRestart` → use `showModal`\n   - `resetImageControls` → use `showModal`\n\n3. **Add preset write modal** on console page:\n   - Input: preset ID + name\n   - Call `set_preset(id, name=name)` via API\n   - Backend API needs to accept `name` parameter\n\nLet me plan the implementation:\n\n### Step 1: Add unified modal CSS + JS to index.html\n### Step 2: Add preset write modal to console.html\n### Step 3: Update router.py to accept name parameter\n### Step 4: Replace all existing modals\n\nLet me start coding. The key design:\n\n```javascript\nwindow.showModal = function(options) {\n    // options: { title, content (html string), onConfirm, onCancel, confirmText, cancelText, showCancel }\n    // Returns: modal element (so caller can close it)\n    \n    // Create overlay that blocks everything\n    // - z-index: 10000\n    // - pointer-events: all on overlay\n    // - Click on overlay does NOT close\n    // - ESC key closes\n    // - Cancel button closes\n    // - Confirm button calls onConfirm then closes\n}\n```\n\nLet me implement this cleanly.\n\nFor the backend, the `set_preset` endpoint currently doesn't accept a name. I need to add it.\n\nLet me look at the backend more carefully:\n\n```python\n@api_router.post(\"/ptz/{device_id}/preset/{preset_id}/set\", summary=\"保存预置位\", tags=[\"PTZ\"])\nasync def ptz_set_preset(device_id: str, preset_id: int) -> dict:\n    ...\n    result = mgr.set_preset(target_ip, preset_id=preset_id)\n```\n\nAnd `mgr.set_preset` calls `PTZController.set_preset(preset_id, name=\"\")` with empty name.\n\nI need to:\n1. Add optional `name` query/body parameter to the endpoint\n2. Pass it through to `PTZController.set_preset`\n\nLet me check the mgr.set_preset method:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me check the mgr.set_preset method chain:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_rb1m2v58qs2f2ht5e5xargm7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && Select-String -Path src -Pattern \"def set_preset\" -AllMatches | Select-Object -First 10 LineNumber,Line,Filename"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":71825,"output":675,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72500,"cost":{"input":0.071825,"output":0.00216,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.073985}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782643542135,"responseId":"cht000d3be9@dx19f0dd611d0b91a122"}}
