{"type":"message","id":"6ae635bf","parentId":"57e4f01f","timestamp":"2026-06-28T10:53:42.979Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to:\n\n1. Replace the old CSS `.modal-backdrop` and `.modal` classes with a unified modal CSS\n2. Replace `showAlert`, `showConfirm` with a unified `showModal` component\n3. Replace `showQuickAddModal` to use the unified modal\n4. Replace `confirmRestart` to use the unified modal instead of browser `confirm()`\n5. Add a new \"写入预置点\" modal dialog on console page\n6. Replace `resetImageControls` in console.html to use the unified modal\n\nLet me plan the unified showModal component:\n\n```js\nwindow.showModal = function(options) {\n    // options: { title, content, buttons, onClose, backdropClosable, escClosable }\n    // Returns the modal element for programmatic closing\n}\n```\n\nActually let me keep it simple. The unified modal:\n- Always has a backdrop (gray overlay)\n- Backdrop is NOT clickable (only ESC or buttons close)\n- ESC closes the modal\n- Returns a close function\n\nLet me think about the approach:\n\n1. CSS: Replace `.modal-backdrop` / `.modal` with a unified `.astro-modal-backdrop` + `.astro-modal` style\n2. JS: Create a single `showModal(options)` function that:\n   - Creates backdrop + modal content\n   - `options.title` - title text\n   - `options.body` - HTML string for body\n   - `options.buttons` - array of {text, class, callback}\n   - `options.escClosable` - default true\n   - Returns {close: fn, element: el}\n\nThen:\n- `showAlert` → calls `showModal({title, body, buttons: [{text:'确定', class:'btn-primary', callback:close}]})`\n- `showConfirm` → calls `showModal({title, body, buttons: [{text:'取消', class:'btn-secondary'}, {text:'确定', class:'btn-primary', callback:onConfirm}]})`\n- `showQuickAddModal` → calls `showModal({title:'添加设备', body: formHTML, buttons: [...]})`\n- `confirmRestart` → calls `showModal` instead of `confirm()`\n- `resetImageControls` → calls `showModal` instead of `confirm()`\n\nFor the preset set modal:\n- Need a form with preset ID + name inputs\n- Calls `apiPost('/api/v1/ptz/' + dev + '/preset/' + id + '/set?name=' + encodeURIComponent(name))`\n\nWait, the current API is `POST /preset/{preset_id}/set` with preset_id in the path. Since I added `name: str = \"\"` as a query parameter to the FastAPI endpoint, I need to pass name as query parameter.\n\nActually looking at the FastAPI route: `async def ptz_set_preset(device_id: str, preset_id: int, name: str = \"\")`, FastAPI will interpret `name` as a query parameter since it's not in the path. So the frontend can call it as `/preset/10/set?name=MyPreset`.\n\nNow let me design the unified modal. I'll keep it clean and simple.\n\nI'll:\n1. Replace the CSS modal-backdrop/modal classes\n2. Replace showAlert/showConfirm/quickAddModal with unified showModal\n3. Add preset set modal button + modal\n4. Fix confirmRestart\n5. Fix resetImageControls in console.html\n\nLet me write the unified showModal function and replace everything step by step.\n\nFirst, let me replace the CSS:\n\n```css\n/* Unified Modal */\n.astro-modal-backdrop { position:fixed; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:100%; background:rgba(0,0,0,0.65); z-index:10000; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }\n.astro-modal { background:#1a1e2e; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:12px; padding:24px; min-width:320px; max-width:480px; box-shadow:0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.6); }\n.astro-modal-title { margin:0 0 16px 0; font-size:18px; }\n.astro-modal-body { margin-bottom:20px; color:#e0e6f0; line-height:1.6; font-size:14px; }\n.astro-modal-actions { display:flex; gap:12px; justify-content:flex-end; }\n```\n\nThen the JS unified showModal:\n\n```js\nwindow.showModal = function(options) {\n    var title = options.title || '';\n    var body = options.body || '';\n    var titleColor = options.titleColor || '#58a6ff';\n    var buttons = options.buttons || [];\n    var modalId = 'astroModal_' + Date.now();\n    \n    var btnHtml = '';\n    buttons.forEach(function(btn) {\n        var cls = btn.cls || 'btn-secondary';\n        var onclick = 'window._modalClose(\"' + modalId + '\", ' + (btn.callback ? 'true' : 'false') + ')';\n        btnHtml += '<button class=\"btn ' + cls + '\" onclick=\"' + onclick + '\">' + btn.text + '</button>';\n    });\n    \n    var html = '<div id=\"' + modalId + '\" class=\"astro-modal-backdrop\">' +\n        '<div class=\"astro-modal\">' +\n        '<h3 class=\"astro-modal-title\" style=\"color:' + titleColor + '\">' + title + '</h3>' +\n        '<div class=\"astro-modal-body\">' + body + '</div>' +\n        '<div class=\"astro-modal-actions\">' + btnHtml + '</div>' +\n        '</div></div>';\n    \n    document.body.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', html);\n    \n    // Store callbacks\n    window._modalCallbacks = window._modalCallbacks || {};\n    window._modalCallbacks[modalId] = buttons;\n    \n    // ESC handler\n    var escHandler = function(e) {\n        if (e.key === 'Escape') {\n            window._modalClose(modalId, false);\n        }\n    };\n    document.addEventListener('keydown', escHandler, {once: true});\n    window._modalEscHandlers = window._modalEscHandlers || {};\n    window._modalEscHandlers[modalId] = escHandler;\n    \n    return modalId;\n};\n\nwindow._modalClose = function(modalId, triggerCallback) {\n    var modal = document.getElementById(modalId);\n    if (!modal) return;\n    \n    // Remove ESC handler\n    if (window._modalEscHandlers && window._modalEscHandlers[modalId]) {\n        document.removeEventListener('keydown', window._modalEscHandlers[modalId]);\n        delete window._modalEscHandlers[modalId];\n    }\n    \n    // Execute callback if needed\n    if (triggerCallback && window._modalCallbacks && window._modalCallbacks[modalId]) {\n        var buttons = window._modalCallbacks[modalId];\n        // Find button with callback\n        for (var i = 0; i < buttons.length; i++) {\n            if (buttons[i].callback) {\n                buttons[i].callback();\n                break;\n            }\n        }\n        delete window._modalCallbacks[modalId];\n    }\n    \n    modal.remove();\n};\n\nwindow.showAlert = function(message, title) {\n    showModal({\n        title: title || '提示',\n        titleColor: '#f0883e',\n        body: '<p>' + message + '</p>',\n        buttons: [{text: '确定', cls: 'btn-primary'}]\n    });\n};\n\nwindow.showConfirm = function(message, onConfirm, title) {\n    showModal({\n        title: title || '确认',\n        titleColor: '#58a6ff',\n        body: '<p>' + message + '</p>',\n        buttons: [\n            {text: '取消', cls: 'btn-secondary'},\n            {text: '确定', cls: 'btn-primary', callback: onConfirm}\n        ]\n    });\n};\n```\n\nWait, I need to be careful. The _modalClose with \"triggerCallback\" — I need to pass which button to trigger. Let me redesign.\n\nActually let me simplify: each button can have its own callback. When a button is clicked:\n1. The callback (if any) is called\n2. The modal is closed\n\nLet me redesign:\n\n```js\nwindow._modalCallbacks = {};\n\nwindow._modalClose = function(modalId, callbackIndex) {\n    var callbacks = window._modalCallbacks[modalId];\n    if (!callbacks) return;\n    \n    var cb = callbacks[callbackIndex];\n    if (cb) cb();\n    \n    // Cleanup\n    delete window._modalCallbacks[modalId];\n    var modal = document.getElementById(modalId);\n    if (modal) modal.remove();\n};\n\nwindow.showModal = function(options) {\n    var title = options.title || '';\n    var body = options.body || '';\n    var titleColor = options.titleColor || '#58a6ff';\n    var buttons = options.buttons || [];\n    var modalId = 'astroModal_' + Date.now();\n    \n    // Store callbacks by index\n    window._modalCallbacks[modalId] = buttons.map(function(b) { return b.callback || null; });\n    \n    var btnHtml = '';\n    buttons.forEach(function(btn, i) {\n        var cls = btn.cls || 'btn-secondary';\n        btnHtml += '<button class=\"btn ' + cls + '\" onclick=\"window._modalClose(\\'' + modalId + '\\', ' + i + ')\">' + btn.text + '</button>';\n    });\n    \n    var html = '<div id=\"' + modalId + '\" class=\"astro-modal-backdrop\">' +\n        '<div class=\"astro-modal\">' +\n        '<h3 class=\"astro-modal-title\" style=\"color:' + titleColor + '\">' + title + '</h3>' +\n        '<div class=\"astro-modal-body\">' + body + '</div>' +\n        '<div class=\"astro-modal-actions\">' + btnHtml + '</div>' +\n        '</div></div>';\n    \n    document.body.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', html);\n    \n    // ESC handler\n    var escHandler = function(e) {\n        if (e.key === 'Escape') {\n            window._modalClose(modalId, -1);  // -1 = no callback\n        }\n    };\n    document.addEventListener('keydown', escHandler, {once: true});\n    \n    return modalId;\n};\n```\n\nThis is clean. Now I need to modify:\n\n1. CSS — replace modal-backdrop/modal with unified styles\n2. showAlert/showConfirm — replace with wrapper around showModal\n3. showQuickAddModal — replace\n4. confirmRestart — replace confirm() with showModal\n5. Add preset set modal\n\nLet me write the full changes.\n\nFirst, let me replace the CSS and showAlert/showConfirm in index.html. Then the quickAddModal. Then the confirmRestart. Then add the preset modal.\n\nActually, I realize I should also add the preset set button to the main console page. Looking at the console.html, the preston section has:\n```html\n<button class=\"btn btn-primary btn-sm\" onclick=\"ptzGotoSelectedPreset()\">前往</button>\n<button class=\"btn btn-warning btn-sm\" onclick=\"ptzSetSelectedPreset()\">保存</button>\n```\n\nThe current \"保存\" button calls `ptzSetSelectedPreset()` which just saves current position as the selected preset. I need to add a \"写入\" button that opens a modal for entering preset ID and name.\n\nLet me check how the console.html presets section currently works. The \"保存\" button uses `ptzSetSelectedPreset()` which reads the dropdown value and saves current position as that preset.\n\nThe new \"写入\" button should open a modal where user can:\n1. Enter preset ID number\n2. Enter preset name\n3. Confirm → calls set_preset with name\n\nLet me now make all the changes. I'll do them as targeted edits.\n\nLet me start with the CSS change, then the JS components.\n\nActually, thinking about this more carefully, I should NOT replace `showAlert` and `showConfirm` entirely because they're called from many places. I'll just rewrite them as thin wrappers around `showModal`. Same for `showQuickAddModal`.\n\nHere's my plan:\n1. Replace CSS block (modal-backdrop/modal) with unified styles\n2. Replace the existing showAlert/showConfirm block with unified showModal + wrappers  \n3. Replace showQuickAddModal\n4. Replace confirmRestart's confirm() call\n5. Add \"写入\" button in console.html presets section\n6. Add ptzPresetWrite function + modal\n7. Replace confirm() in console.html resetImageControls\n\nLet me start.\n\nFor step 1, replace lines 152-156 (CSS):\n\nOld:\n```css\n        /* Modal */\n        .modal-backdrop { position:fixed; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:100%; background:rgba(0,0,0,0.6); z-index:9000; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }\n        .modal { background:#161b22; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:12px; padding:24px; width:400px; max-width:90vw; }\n        .modal h3 { margin-bottom:16px; font-size:18px; }\n        .modal .btn-group { justify-content:flex-end; margin-top:20px; }\n```\n\nNew:\n```css\n        /* Unified Modal (v7.117) */\n        .astro-modal-backdrop { position:fixed; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:100%; background:rgba(0,0,0,0.65); z-index:10000; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }\n        .astro-modal { background:#1a1e2e; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:12px; padding:24px; min-width:320px; max-width:480px; box-shadow:0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.6); }\n        .astro-modal-title { margin:0 0 16px 0; font-size:18px; font-weight:600; }\n        .astro-modal-body { margin:0 0 20px 0; color:#e0e6f0; line-height:1.6; font-size:14px; }\n        .astro-modal-actions { display:flex; gap:12px; justify-content:flex-end; }\n        .astro-modal-field { margin-bottom:14px; }\n        .astro-modal-field label { display:block; margin-bottom:6px; color:#8b949e; font-size:13px; }\n        .astro-modal-field input { width:100%; padding:10px; background:#0d1117; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:6px; color:#e0e6f0; font-size:14px; box-sizing:border-box; }\n        .astro-modal-field input:focus { outline:none; border-color:#58a6ff; }\n```\n\nFor step 2, replace the showAlert/showConfirm block (lines 413-442):\n\nLet me get the exact text to replace. Key is to be precise.\n\nActually let me think about this differently. The file is 3000+ lines and heavily encoded. I need to be very careful with replacements. Let me use very specific unique strings.\n\nFor CSS, I'll replace:\n```\n        /* Modal */\n        .modal-backdrop {\n```\nthrough to:\n```\n        .modal .btn-group { justify-content:flex-end; margin-top:20px; }\n        /* Loading spinner */\n```\n\nFor JS, I'll replace:\n```\n        // v7.15: 网页级别弹窗\n        window.showAlert = function(message, title) {\n```\nthrough to:\n```\n        window.closeConfirm = function(result) {\n            var modal = document.getElementById('confirmModal');\n            if (modal) modal.remove();\n            if (result && window._confirmCallback) {\n                window._confirmCallback();\n                window._confirmCallback = null;\n            }\n        };\n        \nfunction showStartupProgress() {\n```\n\nLet me make these edits now. I'll be very careful with the exact text matching.\n\nActually wait, the file has Chinese characters encoded in a way I can't easily match. Let me check the exact text by reading it again.\n\nI already read lines 152-156:\n```\n        /* Modal */\n        .modal-backdrop { position:fixed; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:100%; background:rgba(0,0,0,0.6); z-index:9000; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }\n        .modal { background:#161b22; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:12px; padding:24px; width:400px; max-width:90vw; }\n        .modal h3 { margin-bottom:16px; font-size:18px; }\n        .modal .btn-group { justify-content:flex-end; margin-top:20px; }\n```\n\nBut when I use Select-String, Chinese chars show as garbled. So I need to match exactly what the read tool shows me. The read tool showed me clean text. Let me use that.\n\nFor the JS, let me read lines 413-442 again to get exact text...\n\nI already have them:\n```\n        // v7.15: 网页级别弹窗\n        window.showAlert = function(message, title) {\n            var alertHtml = '<div id=\"alertModal\" class=\"modal-overlay\" onclick=\"closeAlert()\" style=\"position:fixed;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;background:rgba(0,0,0,0.7);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;z-index:10000\">' +\n                '<div onclick=\"event.stopPropagation()\" style=\"background:#1a1e2e;padding:24px;border-radius:12px;min-width:300px;max-width:500px;box-shadow:0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5)\">' +\n                '<h3 style=\"margin:0 0 16px 0;color:#f0883e\">' + (title || '提示') + '</h3>' +\n                '<p style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;color:#e0e6f0;line-height:1.6\">' + message + '</p>' +\n                '<button class=\"btn btn-primary\" onclick=\"closeAlert()\" style=\"width:100%\">确定</button></div></div>';\n            document.body.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', alertHtml);\n        };\n        window.closeAlert = function() {\n            var modal = document.getElementById('alertModal');\n            if (modal) modal.remove();\n        };\n        window.showConfirm = function(message, onConfirm, title) {\n            var confirmHtml = '<div id=\"confirmModal\" class=\"modal-overlay\" style=\"position:fixed;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;background:rgba(0,0,0,0.7);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;z-index:10000\">' +\n                '<div onclick=\"event.stopPropagation()\" style=\"background:#1a1e2e;padding:24px;border-radius:12px;min-width:300px;max-width:500px;box-shadow:0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5)\">' +\n                '<h3 style=\"margin:0 0 16px 0;color:#58a6ff\">' + (title || '确认') + '</h3>' +\n                '<p style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;color:#e0e6f0;line-height:1.6\">' + message + '</p>' +\n                '<div style=\"display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:flex-end\">' +\n                '<button class=\"btn btn-secondary\" onclick=\"closeConfirm(false)\">取消</button>' +\n                '<button class=\"btn btn-primary\" onclick=\"closeConfirm(true)\">确定</button></div></div></div>';\n            window._confirmCallback = onConfirm;\n            document.body.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', confirmHtml);\n        };\n        window.closeConfirm = function(result) {\n            var modal = document.getElementById('confirmModal');\n            if (modal) modal.remove();\n            if (result && window._confirmCallback) {\n                window._confirmCallback();\n                window._confirmCallback = null;\n            }\n        };\n```\n\nNow let me compose the replacements. I need to do the CSS and JS edits sequentially since they're in the same file.\n\nLet me check - I need to also handle the `modal-overlay` class used in showQuickAddModal, and the `currentModal` variable. Let me plan the replacements:\n\n1. CSS: Replace the modal classes\n2. JS: Replace showAlert/showConfirm/closeAlert/closeConfirm block\n3. JS: Replace showQuickAddModal\n4. JS: Replace confirmRestart\n5. console.html: Add \"写入\" button\n6. console.html: Add ptzPresetWrite function\n7. console.html: Replace confirm() in resetImageControls\n\nLet me start making the edits. I'll do multiple edit calls.\n\nFirst, the CSS replacement:\n```edit\npath: index.html\noldText:\n        /* Modal */\n        .modal-backdrop { position:fixed; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:100%; background:rgba(0,0,0,0.6); z-index:9000; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }\n        .modal { background:#161b22; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:12px; padding:24px; width:400px; max-width:90vw; }\n        .modal h3 { margin-bottom:16px; font-size:18px; }\n        .modal .btn-group { justify-content:flex-end; margin-top:20px; }\nnewText:\n        /* Unified Modal (v7.117) */\n        .astro-modal-backdrop { position:fixed; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:100%; background:rgba(0,0,0,0.65); z-index:10000; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }\n        .astro-modal { background:#1a1e2e; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:12px; padding:24px; min-width:320px; max-width:480px; box-shadow:0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.6); }\n        .astro-modal-title { margin:0 0 16px 0; font-size:18px; font-weight:600; }\n        .astro-modal-body { margin:0 0 20px 0; color:#e0e6f0; line-height:1.6; font-size:14px; }\n        .astro-modal-actions { display:flex; gap:12px; justify-content:flex-end; }\n        .astro-modal-field { margin-bottom:14px; }\n        .astro-modal-field label { display:block; margin-bottom:6px; color:#8b949e; font-size:13px; }\n        .astro-modal-field input { width:100%; padding:10px; background:#0d1117; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:6px; color:#e0e6f0; font-size:14px; box-sizing:border-box; }\n        .astro-modal-field input:focus { outline:none; border-color:#58a6ff; }\n```\n\nSecond, replace showAlert/showConfirm block. Let me make sure I have the exact old text.\n\nFor showQuickAddModal, let me re-read it to get exact text.\n\nThen I'll also need to handle the `showDeviceInfoModal` which calls `showModal('设备信息', info)` — but that seems to be a different `showModal` that doesn't exist. Looking again:\n\n```js\n        window.showDeviceInfoModal = function(ip) {\n            var d = allDevices.find(function(dev) { return dev.ip === ip; }) || {};\n            var info = ...\n            if (window.showModal) {\n                showModal('设备信息', info);\n            } else {\n                if (window.showAlert) window.showAlert(info, '设备信息');\n            }\n        };\n```\n\nSo there's a reference to `showModal` that doesn't seem to be defined. It falls back to `showAlert`. My new unified `showModal` has a different signature with an options object, so I need to make sure I don't break this. Let me check if `showModal` is defined anywhere...\n\nLooking at the grep results earlier, `showModal` only appears in `showDeviceInfoModal`. So it's dead code that falls back to `showAlert`. Good, my change won't break it since I'm not defining a conflicting `showModal` function (mine is the options-based one). Actually wait, let me update that function too.\n\nOK let me just proceed with the edits. Let me be very careful with each one.\n\nLet me think about what edits I need for the unified modal component. I'll create the showModal function and then rewrite showAlert/showConfirm/closeAlert/closeConfirm/closeQuickAddModal as wrappers.\n\nHere's the plan:\n\n```\nOLD (lines 413-442):\n        // v7.15: 网页级别弹窗\n        window.showAlert = function(...)\n        ...\n        window.closeConfirm = function(result) { ... };\n\nNEW:\n        // v7.117: 统一弹窗组件\n        window._modalCallbacks = {};\n        window._modalClose = function(modalId, callbackIndex) { ... };\n        window.showModal = function(options) { ... };\n        // 便捷方法\n        window.showAlert = function(message, title) { ... };\n        window.showConfirm = function(message, onConfirm, title) { ... };\n```\n\nOK let me also check — the quickAddModal currently uses `onclick=\"closeQuickAddModal(event)\"` on the backdrop. I'll need to replace that whole function with showModal.\n\nFor showQuickAddModal, the body is dynamic (form with inputs). I'll use showModal's `body` option.\n\nBut wait — showQuickAddModal currently has `submitQuickAdd()` which reads form values inside the modal. With the new approach, I need the submit button's callback to read the form values.\n\nLet me think... The submit button callback needs to access `document.getElementById('quickAddIp').value` etc. Those elements will exist inside the modal body. So I can set the submit button's callback to call `submitQuickAdd()` which reads from the DOM. This should work fine since `submitQuickAdd()` also calls `closeQuickAddModal()` — I'll need to update that to close via the unified modal.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: in the submit callback, wrap `submitQuickAdd` logic + close in the callback itself. But `submitQuickAdd` currently calls `closeQuickAddModal()` at the start. I can just have the callback close the modal.\n\nLet me redesign showQuickAddModal:\n\n```js\nwindow.showQuickAddModal = function(ip, gateway) {\n    var localhostGateway = window.localhostGateway || gateway || '';\n    var body = '<div class=\"astro-modal-field\"><label>IP 地址</label><input type=\"text\" id=\"quickAddIp\" value=\"' + (ip || '') + '\"></div>' +\n        '<div class=\"astro-modal-field\"><label>网关</label><input type=\"text\" id=\"quickAddGateway\" value=\"' + localhostGateway + '\"></div>' +\n        '<div class=\"astro-modal-field\"><label>用户名</label><input type=\"text\" id=\"quickAddUser\" value=\"admin\"></div>' +\n        '<div class=\"astro-modal-field\"><label>密码</label><input type=\"password\" id=\"quickAddPass\"></div>';\n    showModal({\n        title: '添加设备',\n        body: body,\n        buttons: [\n            {text: '取消', cls: 'btn-secondary'},\n            {text: '添加并连接', cls: 'btn-primary', callback: function() {\n                var ip = document.getElementById('quickAddIp').value.trim();\n                var gateway = document.getElementById('quickAddGateway').value.trim();\n                var username = document.getElementById('quickAddUser').value.trim();\n                var password = document.getElementById('quickAddPass').value;\n                if (!ip) { addLog('error', '请输入 IP 地址'); return; }\n                if (!password) { addLog('error', '请输入密码'); return; }\n                apiPost('/api/v1/devices', {ip: ip, gateway: gateway, username: username, password: password})\n                    .then(function(result) {\n                        if (result.success) {\n                            addLog('done', '设备已添加: ' + ip);\n                            refreshDevices();\n                            setTimeout(function() { connectDevice(ip); }, 500);\n                        } else {\n                            addLog('error', result.message || '添加失败');\n                        }\n                    }).catch(function(e) { addLog('error', '添加设备失败: ' + e); });\n            }}\n        ]\n    });\n};\n```\n\nOK this is getting complex. Let me just go ahead and do the edits. I'll be methodical.\n\nLet me also think about the confirmRestart replacement. Currently:\n```js\nwindow.confirmRestart = function() {\n    if (!confirm('确定要重启 AstroHub 吗?\\n重启期间服务将暂时不可用。')) return;\n    ...\n};\n```\n\nNew:\n```js\nwindow.confirmRestart = function() {\n    showConfirm('确定要重启 AstroHub 吗?<br>重启期间服务将暂时不可用。', function() {\n        showToast('info', '正在重启...');\n        apiPost('/api/v1/system/restart', null).then(function(r) {\n            if (r && r.success) {\n                showToast('success', '重启中，10秒后自动刷新页面...');\n                setTimeout(function() { location.reload(); }, 10000);\n            } else {\n                showToast('error', r ? r.message : '重启失败');\n            }\n        }).catch(function(e) {\n            showToast('warning', '重启中，10秒后自动刷新页面...');\n            setTimeout(function() { location.reload(); }, 10000);\n        });\n    }, '重启确认');\n};\n```\n\nOK, let me now execute all the edits. I'll do them step by step, verifying each.\n\nLet me start with the CSS replacement in index.html, then the JS components.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"OK, 开始执行改动。CSS 先来。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_apmnhsX1RDwciGciUKw57042","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"oldText":"        /* Modal */\n        .modal-backdrop { position:fixed; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:100%; background:rgba(0,0,0,0.6); z-index:9000; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }\n        .modal { background:#161b22; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:12px; padding:24px; width:400px; max-width:90vw; }\n        .modal h3 { margin-bottom:16px; font-size:18px; }\n        .modal .btn-group { justify-content:flex-end; margin-top:20px; }","newText":"        /* Unified Modal (v7.117) */\n        .astro-modal-backdrop { position:fixed; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:100%; background:rgba(0,0,0,0.65); z-index:10000; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }\n        .astro-modal { background:#1a1e2e; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:12px; padding:24px; min-width:320px; max-width:480px; box-shadow:0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.6); }\n        .astro-modal-title { margin:0 0 16px 0; font-size:18px; font-weight:600; }\n        .astro-modal-body { margin:0 0 20px 0; color:#e0e6f0; line-height:1.6; font-size:14px; }\n        .astro-modal-actions { display:flex; gap:12px; justify-content:flex-end; }\n        .astro-modal-field { margin-bottom:14px; }\n        .astro-modal-field label { display:block; margin-bottom:6px; color:#8b949e; font-size:13px; }\n        .astro-modal-field input { width:100%; padding:10px; background:#0d1117; border:1px solid #30363d; border-radius:6px; color:#e0e6f0; font-size:14px; box-sizing:border-box; }\n        .astro-modal-field input:focus { outline:none; border-color:#58a6ff; }"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\index.html"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":78707,"output":7343,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86050,"cost":{"inp