{"type":"message","id":"39d25be2","parentId":"e7ca0055","timestamp":"2026-06-28T15:41:51.783Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All browser-level confirm/alert/prompt calls have been replaced. Let me now verify the backend changes are correct by checking the router.py change.\n\nLet me also verify the overall structure is clean. Let me do a final review of the changes:\n\n1. **Backend**:\n   - `src/core/ptz_controller.py`: `set_preset()` now accepts `name` parameter, passes to `ctrl.set_preset(preset_id, name=name)`\n   - `src/api/router.py`: `ptz_set_preset()` now accepts `name` query parameter, passes to `mgr.set_preset(target_ip, preset_id=preset_id, name=name)`\n\n2. **Frontend**:\n   - Unified CSS: `.astro-modal-backdrop`, `.astro-modal`, etc.\n   - Unified `showModal()` component with `type: 'alert'|'confirm'|'form'`\n   - ESC key handler\n   - No click-on-backdrop to close\n   - Backward compatible `showAlert`/`showConfirm` wrappers\n   - Replaced all `confirm()` calls: confirmRestart, deleteDevice, resetImageControls, deleteSelected\n   - Replaced all `prompt()` calls: addDeviceInline, modifyIpPrompt, filterFiles, credential prompt\n   - New `ptzWritePreset()` function with form modal\n   - New \"写入\" button in console.html\n   - Exposed `ptzWritePreset` to global scope\n\nLet me verify the router.py change was correct - the `name` parameter needs to be a query parameter since it's a POST endpoint with preset_id in the path.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"全部清除。验证后端改动：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9qc7h0l2k6zyvr0miz5bzy7d","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"offset":1048,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_iu4li4y0ev2rnl3dhmvx1kk6","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":15,"offset":2000,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\core\\ptz_controller.py"}}],"api":"opena