{"type":"message","id":"7384ff75","parentId":"f3e17235","timestamp":"2026-06-28T16:29:20.033Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me fix the speed test bugs systematically. I need to:\n\n1. Fix `router.py`: `results` is a list, not dict. Fix `results.get(\"success\")` and group results properly.\n2. Fix frontend: show error when success:false in result area\n3. Frontend rendering functions already read `speed_map/pan_speed/tilt_speed` - I need the backend to return those keys\n\nLet me backup first, then fix precisely.\n\nThe key changes:\n- `router.py`: Fix the success check and transform results list into the expected dict structure\n- `index.html`: Show error in result area on failure\n\nLet me trace through the code carefully:\n\nIn `run_all_tests()`, the return value is `all_results` which is a `list[dict]` from `post_process_csv()`. Each dict has: axis, direction, speed_level, zoom, speed_val, repeats, etc.\n\nIn `router.py`:\n```python\nresults = await asyncio.to_thread(tester.run_all_tests, None, req.speed_profile)\n...\nreturn {\n    \"success\": results.get(\"success\", False),  # ❌ results is list, .get() returns None\n    \"message\": f\"速度测试完成: {req.device_ip}\",\n    \"results\": results,  # ❌ raw list\n}\n```\n\nFrontend expects:\n- `resp.results` to have keys: `speed_map`, `pan_speed`, `tilt_speed`, `total_tests`\n\nI need to transform the list into the expected dict format in `router.py`, not in `run_all_tests` (to avoid breaking the standalone CLI usage which returns list).\n\nThe grouping logic:\n- `speed_map`: for each speed_level, average speed_val across all axes, directions, zooms\n- `pan_speed`: for each speed_level, average Pan speed_val across all directions, zooms  \n- `tilt_speed`: for each speed_level, average Tilt speed_val across all directions, zooms\n\nWait, looking at the frontend more carefully:\n```js\nfunction _renderSpeedTable(title, speedMap) {\n    var keys = Object.keys(speedMap);\n    keys.forEach(function(k) {\n        h += '<tr><td>' + k + '</td><td>' + speedMap[k] + '</td></tr>';\n    });\n}\n```\n\nIt expects `speed_map` to be `{speed_level: speed_val}`, simple key-value pairs. The frontend just displays them in a table. This is fine.\n\nLet me now write the fix. The grouping should be done once in `router.py` before returning.\n\nAlso need to fix the success:false rendering in the frontend.\n\nFor `speedTestRun()` in index.html:\n```js\nif (resp && resp.success) {\n    ...\n    renderSpeedResults(resp.results || {});\n} else {\n    showToast('error', resp ? resp.message : '测试失败');\n    addLog('error', '速度测试失败: ' + (resp ? resp.message : '未知'));\n}\n```\n\nThis already shows a toast, but doesn't update the result area. I should make it show the error in the result area too.\n\nFor `connectSpeedTestRun()`:\n```js\nif (resp && resp.success) {\n    ...\n} else {\n    showToast('error', resp ? resp.message : '测试失败');\n    ...\n    document.getElementById('connectSpeedResultMini').innerHTML = '... error ...';\n}\n```\n\nThis already updates `connectSpeedResultMini`, but not the full result area. Let me check...\n\nActually looking more carefully, `connectSpeedTestRun` already sets the error in `connectSpeedResultMini`. But the full results area (`connectFullResultArea`) isn't updated on error. That's less critical - the main `speedTestRun` function is the one the boss called out.\n\nOK, my plan:\n\n1. Backup\n2. `router.py`: Fix `results.get(\"success\")` → `len(results) > 0`, and transform list to dict\n3. `index.html`: In `speedTestRun`, update result area on failure\n4. `index.html`: In `connectSpeedTestRun`, update full result area on failure\n\nLet me keep it minimal. No new functions, no extra imports - just transform the data.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"备份先。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_AYNc6JV9UXgiReYejTPn6604","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-fac