{"type":"message","id":"7cd81045","parentId":"9abca783","timestamp":"2026-06-28T16:29:59.471Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me plan the fixes:\n\n1. `router.py:2641` — `results.get(\"success\")` → `len(results) > 0` (results is a list)\n2. `router.py:2642` — Group the list into `{speed_map, pan_speed, tilt_speed, total_tests}` before returning\n3. `index.html:920-925` — On `success:false`, show error in result area too\n4. Frontend rendering — should work once data format matches\n5. Add by_zoom dimension — the frontend currently renders `speed_map`, `pan_speed`, `tilt_speed`. I need to group the results correctly.\n\nLet me carefully design the grouping function in router.py. The data format from `post_process_csv` returns a list of dicts like:\n```python\n{\n    \"mac\": mac,\n    \"axis\": axis,          # \"pan\" or \"tilt\"\n    \"direction\": direction, # 1 or -1\n    \"speed_level\": speed_level,\n    \"speed_val\": round(avg_speed, 2),\n    \"hit_limit\": hit_limit_flag,\n    \"zoom\": zoom,\n    \"repeats\": len(speeds),\n    \"movement_direction\": movement_direction,\n    \"direction_info\": direction_info,\n}\n```\n\nFor `speed_map`: average all speeds at each speed_level (across all axes, directions, zooms)\nFor `pan_speed`: average all pan speeds at each speed_level\nFor `tilt_speed`: average all tilt speeds at each speed_level\n\nThe frontend expects:\n- `speed_map`: `{speed_level: speed_val, ...}`\n- `pan_speed`: `{speed_level: speed_val, ...}`\n- `tilt_speed`: `{speed_level: speed_val, ...}`\n\nSo I need to group by speed_level, averaging across directions and zooms.\n\nLet me keep it simple - just group the data in the router before returning. I'll add a small helper.\n\nActually, let me re-read the frontend to make sure I know exactly what it expects...\n\nFrom renderSpeedResults:\n```js\nvar speedMap = results.speed_map || results.speed_mapping || {};\nhtml += _renderSpeedTable('📊 总体', speedMap);\nvar panMap = results.pan_speed || {};\nhtml += _renderSpeedTable('🔵 Pan轴', panMap);\nvar tiltMap = results.tilt_speed || {};\nhtml += _renderSpeedTable('🟠 Tilt轴', tiltMap);\n```\n\nAnd _renderSpeedTable:\n```js\nfunction _renderSpeedTable(title, speedMap) {\n    var keys = Object.keys(speedMap);\n    // renders table with speed_level -> speed_val\n}\n```\n\nSo the format is: `{speed_level_value: speed_val_number, ...}`\n\nNow for the grouping in router.py, I need:\n- `speed_map`: group by speed_level, average all speed_vals\n- `pan_speed`: group by speed_level where axis==\"pan\", average speed_vals\n- `tilt_speed`: group by speed_level where axis==\"tilt\", average speed_vals\n\nThis is the simplest approach. No extra files, no extra libraries.\n\nLet me also fix the `total_tests` field — the frontend reads `results.total_tests`:\n```js\nhtml += '<div class=\"status-row\"><span class=\"status-label\">测试总数</span><span class=\"status-value\">' + (results.total_tests || '--') + '</span></div>';\n```\n\nSo I need to include `total_tests` in the returned results dict.\n\nNow the router fix:\n- `results` is a list from `run_all_tests`\n- `success = len(results) > 0`\n- Group into dict with speed_map, pan_speed, tilt_speed, total_tests\n- On fail, return `{\"success\": False, \"message\": \"...\"}`\n\nThe frontend fix for error display - when `success: false`:\nCurrently:\n```js\n} else {\n    showToast('error', resp ? resp.message : '测试失败');\n    addLog('error', '速度测试失败: ' + (resp ? resp.message : '未知'));\n}\n```\n\nNeed to also show the error in result area:\n```js\n} else {\n    showToast('error', resp ? resp.message : '测试失败');\n    addLog('error', '速度测试失败: ' + (resp ? resp.message : '未知'));\n    var area = document.getElementById('speedResultArea');\n    if (area) area.innerHTML = '<div class=\"advanced-status-panel\"><p style=\"color:#f85149\">❌ ' + (resp ? resp.message : '测试失败') + '</p></div>';\n}\n```\n\nSame for the connectDevice version.\n\nLet me implement this.",