{"type":"message","id":"352695a2","parentId":"7cd81045","timestamp":"2026-06-28T16:29:59.478Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_nVkXxRmKwzLmswkQeiFH4682","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        tester = SpeedTester(ptz)\r\n        global _active_speed_tester\r\n        _active_speed_tester = tester\r\n        try:\r\n            import asyncio\r\n            results = await asyncio.to_thread(tester.run_all_tests, None, req.speed_profile)\r\n        finally:\r\n            _active_speed_tester = None\r\n\r\n        # v7.51: CSV 已通过 device_path 写入，JSON 摘要写入 mac_clean 目录\r\n        mac_clean = mac.replace(':', '').lower() if mac else \"unknown\"\r\n        config_saved = False\r\n        try:\r\n            store.save_speed_results(mac_clean, results)\r\n            config_saved = True\r\n        except Exception:\r\n            pass\r\n\r\n        return {\r\n            \"success\": results.get(\"success\", False),\r\n            \"message\": f\"速度测试完成: {req.device_ip}\",\r\n            \"results\": results,\r\n            \"config_saved\": config_saved,\r\n            \"mac\": mac,\r\n        }\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"速度测试异常: {e}\"}\r\n\r\n\r\n_active_speed_tester: Any = None\r\n\r\n\r\n@api_router.post(\"/advanced/speed/cancel\", summary=\"取消速度测试\", tags=[\"Advanced\"])\r\nasync def advanced_speed_cancel(device_ip: str = Query(default=\"\")) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"取消正在运行的速度测试。\"\"\"\r\n    global _active_speed_tester\r\n    if _active_speed_tester is not None:\r\n        _active_speed_tester.cancel()\r\n        _active_speed_tester = None\r\n        return {\"success\": True, \"message\": \"速度测试已取消\"}\r\n    return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"没有正在运行的速度测试\"}\r\n\r\n\r\n@api_router.get(\"/advanced/speed/status\", summary=\"获取速度测试状态\", tags=[\"Advanced\"])\r\nasync def advanced_speed_status(device_ip: str = Query(default=\"\")) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"获取设备速度测试状态。\"\"\"\r\n    if not device_ip:\r\n        return {\"success\": True, \"status\": {}}\r\n    try:\r\n        from src.ptz.isapi.client import ISAPIClient\r\n        from src.advanced.speed import SpeedTester\r\n\r\n        ptz_mgr: PTZDeviceController | None = _managers.get(\"ptz_controller\")  # type: ignore[assignment]\r\n        creds = ptz_mgr.get_credentials(device_ip) if ptz_mgr else None\r\n        if not creds:\r\n\n[1361 more lines in file. Use offset=2676 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782664199478}}
{"type":"message","id":"b8f9c2d7","parentId":"352695a2","timestamp":"2026-06-28T16:30:57.246Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me plan the precise fix:\n\n1. `router.py:2631-2645` — Fix `results.get(\"success\")` (list has no .get), add grouping into `{speed_map, pan_speed, tilt_speed, by_zoom}` \n2. `index.html:920-925` — Fix `success:false` to show error in result area\n3. `index.html:953-970` — No change needed (it reads `speed_map/pan_speed/tilt_speed` from results which will now exist after backend fix)\n\nActually, let me think about what the frontend rendering needs. The current render functions expect:\n- `results.speed_map` → `{speed_level: speed_val}` \n- `results.pan_speed` → `{speed_level: speed_val}`\n- `results.tilt_speed` → `{speed_level: speed_val}`\n\nAnd the table renders: `速度档位 | 实际速率 (°/s)`.\n\nSo in `router.py`, I need to transform the `list[dict]` (each dict has `{axis, direction, speed_level, zoom, speed_val, ...}`) into:\n- `speed_map`: average across all axes/zooms for each speed_level\n- `pan_speed`: average across all zooms for each speed_level on pan axis  \n- `tilt_speed`: same for tilt\n- `by_zoom`: zoom-dimension grouping\n\nThen pass this wrapped structure as `results`.\n\nLet me write the fix for router.py:\n\n```python\n        # 将 results 数组分组为前端所需格式\n        success = isinstance(results, list) and len(results) > 0\n        formatted_results = {}\n        if success:\n            by_zoom = {}\n            for r in results:\n                zoom = r.get(\"zoom\", 0)\n                axis = r.get(\"axis\", \"\")\n                sl = r.get(\"speed_level\", 0)\n                sv = r.get(\"speed_val\", 0.0)\n                by_zoom.setdefault(zoom, {}).setdefault(axis, {})[str(sl)] = sv\n\n            # speed_map: 所有zoom+axis的平均\n            speed_map = {}\n            for r in results:\n                sl = str(r.get(\"speed_level\", 0))\n                if sl not in speed_map:\n                    speed_map[sl] = []\n                speed_map[sl].append(r.get(\"speed_val\", 0.0))\n            for k, v in speed_map.items():\n                speed_map[k] = round(sum(v) / len(v), 2)\n\n            # pan_speed / tilt_speed: 各轴所有zoom平均\n            pan_speed = {}\n            tilt_speed = {}\n            for r in results:\n                sl = str(r.get(\"speed_level\", 0))\n                sv = r.get(\"speed_val\", 0.0)\n                if r.get(\"axis\") == \"pan\":\n                    pan_speed.setdefault(sl, []).append(sv)\n                elif r.get(\"axis\") == \"tilt\":\n                    tilt_speed.setdefault(sl, []).append(sv)\n            for k, v in pan_speed.items():\n                pan_speed[k] = round(sum(v) / len(v), 2)\n            for k, v in tilt_speed.items():\n                tilt_speed[k] = round(sum(v) / len(v), 2)\n\n            formatted_results = {\n                \"speed_map\": speed_map,\n                \"pan_speed\": pan_speed,\n                \"tilt_speed\": tilt_speed,\n                \"by_zoom\": by_zoom,\n                \"total_tests\": len(results),\n            }\n```\n\nWait, but the boss said \"禁止过度开发\". This grouping is necessary to fix the frontend, but it's at the boundary between backend and frontend. \n\nActually, let me reconsider. The boss said to fix 5 items. Let me re-read:\n\n1. `success:false` → show error  \n2. Return format wrong → should return P/T per zoom\n3. Check calculation logic → it's already correct (首尾坐标/时间)\n4. Fix rendering → data structure mismatch\n5. Zoom dimension\n\nThe grouping logic is necessary - it's not \"extra\", it IS the fix. Without it the frontend can't display anything.\n\nLet me do a clean, minimal fix:\n\n1. `router.py`: Replace the broken return with grouped dict\n2. `index.html`: Fix error display when success:false\n\nThat's 2 edits, minimal.\n\nFor the frontend: The current render functions already read `speed_map`, `pan_speed`, `tilt_speed` from the results object