r in `connectSpeedResultMini`. But it doesn't clear `connectFullResultArea`. Let me check if that's an issue... The full result area might show stale data. But the user asked for minimal changes, so I'll leave it.\n\nActually wait, I should also check if `connectSpeedTestRun` calls `renderConnectFullResults` which also has the same data format issue. Let me re-read that code...\n\nLooking at the code:\n```javascript\nif (resp && resp.success) {\n    showToast('success', '速度检测完成');\n    addLog('success', '速度检测完成: ' + (resp.message || ''));\n    renderConnectSpeedResultMini(resp.results || {});\n    renderConnectFullResults(resp.results || {}, 'speed');\n}\n```\n\n`renderConnectFullResults` for speed:\n```javascript\n} else if (type === 'speed') {\n    var speedMap = results.speed_map || results.speed_mapping || {};\n    html += _renderSpeedTable('📊 总体', speedMap);\n    var panMap = results.pan_speed || {};\n    html += _renderSpeedTable('🔵 Pan轴', panMap);\n    var tiltMap = results.tilt_speed || {};\n    html += _renderSpeedTable('🟠 Tilt轴', tiltMap);\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThis now matches the new format. Good.\n\nAnd `renderConnectSpeedResultMini`:\n```javascript\nfunction renderConnectSpeedResultMini(results) {\n    var area = document.getElementById('connectSpeedResultMini');\n    var speedMap = results.speed_map || results.speed_mapping || {};\n    var count = Object.keys(speedMap).length;\n    var total = results.total_tests || '--';\n    area.innerHTML = '<span style=\"font-size:12px;color:#f0883e\">✅ ' + count + ' 个速度档位 (' + total + ' 项测试)</span>';\n}\n```\n\nThis also matches. Good.\n\nI think the changes are complete. Let me verify no issues remain.\n\nActually, I realize I should also check: when `success` is False in the router, the `results` field will be `{}` (empty dict from `formatted = {}`). The frontend checks `resp.success` first, so it won't try to render the empty results. But the `renderSpeedResults` function has a guard: `if (!results || Object.keys(results).length === 0)` which would show \"暂无结果\". Since the frontend checks `resp.success` first, this path won't be reached. Good.\n\nWait, actually there's a subtle issue. When `success` is False, `formatted = {}`, and the frontend does:\n```javascript\nif (resp && resp.success) {\n    renderSpeedResults(resp.results || {});\n} else {\n    // show error\n}\n```\n\nSo `renderSpeedResults` is only called when `success` is True, and in that case `formatted` will have the proper structure. Good.\n\nLet me now verify the final state of all changes.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"验证最终状态：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kaq0n5rj1h28gk3loius7iws","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"\nimport ast, sys\n# Check router.py syntax\nwith open('src/api/router.py', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    try: ast.parse(f.read()); print('router.py: OK')\n    except SyntaxError as e: print(f'router.py: FAIL - {e}'); sys.exit(1)\n# Check speed.py syntax\nwith open('src/advanced/speed.py', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    try: ast.parse(f.read()); print('speed.py: OK')\n    except SyntaxError as e: print(f'speed.py: FAIL - {e}'); sys.exit(1)\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":114851,"output":1326,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116177,"cost":{"input":0.114851,"output":0.004243200000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1190942}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782664603304,"responseId":"cht000de28a@dx19f0f177617b828262"}}
