{"type":"message","id":"a5b312d1","parentId":"d5f578cd","timestamp":"2026-06-28T17:10:16.040Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The boss wants me to add Zoom dimension display to the speed test results. Let me look at the current rendering and the data structure to design the right approach.\n\nCurrent `_renderSpeedTable` renders a simple 2-column table: speed_level → speed_val.\n\nThe `by_zoom` data structure is: `{zoom_val: {pan: {speed_level: val}, tilt: {speed_level: val}}}`\n\nI need to modify `renderSpeedResults` to show results grouped by zoom. The cleanest approach: add a zoom-grouped table that shows for each zoom level, the pan and tilt speeds side by side.\n\nLet me think about the best layout. The boss wants:\n- Different Z values showing different P and T speeds\n- Format like: 项目 支持 范围\n\nSo a table like:\n| Zoom | Pan速度档位 | Pan速率 (°/s) | Tilt速度档位 | Tilt速率 (°/s) |\n\nOr better, per zoom:\n| 速度档位 | Pan (°/s) | Tilt (°/s) |\n\nLet me keep it simple. Modify `renderSpeedResults` to add zoom-grouped tables after the existing overall tables.\n\nThe `by_zoom` structure: `{10: {pan: {\"1\": 0.5, \"50\": 25.0, \"100\": 50.0}, tilt: {\"1\": 0.3, ...}}, 165: {...}, 320: {...}}`\n\nI'll add a section that shows per-zoom tables. Each zoom level gets a table with columns: 速度档位 | Pan (°/s) | Tilt (°/s).\n\nLet me also update `renderConnectFullResults` for the speed type to include zoom data.\n\nLet me read the full renderConnectFullResults for speed type.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"先看完整渲染逻辑，确保改对。\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_aj8zuxkwf0niztzqg7620toq","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":30,"offset":1265,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\index.html"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":116291,"output":488,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116779,"cost":{"input":0.11629099999999999,"output":0.