{"type":"message","id":"cd83a03d","parentId":"29135e36","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:33:10.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is showing me that the speed test results are still displaying incorrectly - showing \"项目 支持 范围\" with \"0 N -~-\" rows. This is the old function test format, not the speed test format. Let me trace through the code to find why.\n\nThe issue is in `advanced.html` - the `renderAdvResult` function. Let me trace the data flow:\n\n1. `advanced.html` calls `/api/v1/advanced/detect/start` \n2. This runs the speed test and stores results in `detect_tasks[task_id][\"results\"][\"speed\"]`\n3. The poll gets the result from `/api/v1/advanced/detect/result/{task_id}`\n4. This returns `{\"success\": True, \"results\": {\"speed\": speed_result}}`\n5. Then `renderAdvResult(data)` is called with `data = {\"success\": True, \"results\": {\"speed\": speed_result}}`\n\nIn `renderAdvResult`:\n```javascript\nconst results = data.functions || data.results || data;\n```\n\nSo `results` = `data.results` = `{\"speed\": speed_result}`\n\nThen it checks:\n```javascript\nif (results.pan_min !== undefined || results.tilt_min !== undefined) {\n    // limit test\n} else if (results.speed_map !== undefined || results.pan_speed !== undefined) {\n    // speed test\n} else {\n    // function test (FALLBACK!)\n}\n```\n\nBut `results` = `{\"speed\": speed_result}`, which has no `pan_min`, no `speed_map`, no `pan_speed` - so it falls through to the function test else branch!\n\nThe problem is that the detect API wraps results as `{\"speed\": speed_result}`, but `renderAdvResult` expects the speed data at the top level.\n\nLet me also check what `speed_result` looks like. The detect task stores `results[\"speed\"] = speed_result` where `speed_result` is the return of `run_all_tests`. But wait - in the detect flow, the `advanced_speed_run` endpoint isn't called. The detect flow directly calls `speed_tester.run_all_tests()`.\n\nLet me re-read the detect code:\n```python\nspeed_result = await asyncio.to_thread(speed_tester.run_all_tests, None, req.speed_profile, speed_progress_callback)\nif not speed_result:\n    detect_tasks[task_id].update(status=\"failed\", current_step=\"speed: 无结果\")\n    return\nresults[\"speed\"] = speed_result\n```\n\nAnd `run_all_tests` returns a list of dicts (from `post_process_csv`). So `results[\"speed\"]` = list of dicts.\n\nThen the detect result endpoint returns:\n```python\nreturn {\"success\": True, \"results\": task.get(\"results\", {})}\n```\n\nSo the frontend gets: `{\"success\": True, \"results\": {\"speed\": [list of dicts]}}`\n\nThen `renderAdvResult(data)`:\n- `results = data.results` = `{\"speed\": [list of dicts]}`\n- `results.pan_min` = undefined\n- `results.speed_map` = undefined  \n- `results.pan_speed` = undefined\n- Falls to else branch → function test format → shows \"项目 支持 范围\" with each key of `{\"speed\": [...]}` → \"speed\" is an array, so `typeof val === 'object'` is true, but `val.label` is undefined, `val.supported` is undefined → shows \"N\" and \"-~-\"\n\nThat's the bug. The detect flow stores raw `run_all_tests` output (list), not the processed dict format.\n\nThe fix should be in the detect task code in router.py - it needs to process the speed results the same way `advanced_speed_run` does.\n\nLet me look at how `advanced_speed_run` processes results:\n\n```python\nresults = await asyncio.to_thread(tester.run_all_tests, None, req.speed_profile)\n# ... then it processes results into dict format\n```\n\nBut in the detect flow, `speed_result` is just stored raw. We need to apply the same processing.\n\nLet me also check: is the user seeing this from the \"高级测试\" page or the \"主控台\" page? The output format \"项目 支持 范围\" with \"0 N -~-\" matches the `renderAdvResult` function in `advanced.html`, which is the 高级测试 page.\n\nSo the fix is in `router.py` detect flow, around line 2856-2866. We need to process `speed_result` (list) into the dict format before storing it.\n\nLet me also check if there's a `renderAdvResult` that gets called from the poll callback. Let me look at the poll function.\n\nActually wait, let me re-read the poll flow more carefully. The poll calls `/api/v1/advanced/detect/result/{task_id}` which returns `{\"success\": True, \"results\": {\"speed\": speed_result}}`. Then `renderAdvResult` is called with this data.\n\nBut the issue is two-fold:\n1. The detect API wraps results as `{\"speed\": [...]}` (raw list)\n2. `renderAdvResult` expects speed data at the top level of `results`\n\nThe simplest fix: in the detect flow, process `speed_result` the same way `advanced_speed_run` does, OR fix `renderAdvResult` to unwrap the nested structure.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the detect result endpoint:\n```python\nreturn {\"success\": True, \"results\": task.get(\"results\", {})}\n```\n\nThis returns `{\"success\": True, \"results\": {\"speed\": [list]}}`.\n\nThen `renderAdvResult(data)` does:\n```javascript\nconst results = data.functions || data.results || data;\n// results = {\"speed\": [list]}\n```\n\nThe cleanest fix: process the speed results in the detect flow to match the format that `renderAdvResult` expects. Let me look at what `advanced_speed_run` does to process results:\n\n```python\n# v7.118: 将list结果分组为dict\nif isinstance(results, list):\n    speed_map = {}\n    pan_map = {}\n    tilt_map = {}\n    by_zoom = {}\n    for r in results:\n        sl = str(r.get(\"speed_level\", \"\"))\n        ax = r.get(\"axis\", \"\")\n        sv = r.get(\"speed_val\", 0)\n        zm = r.get(\"zoom\", 0)\n        if sl:\n            if sl not in speed_map:\n                speed_map[sl] = []\n            speed_map[sl].append(sv)\n        if ax == \"pan\" and sl:\n            if sl not in pan_map:\n                pan_map[sl] = []\n            pan_map[sl].append(sv)\n        if ax == \"tilt\" and sl:\n            if sl not in tilt_map:\n                tilt_map[sl] = []\n            tilt_map[sl].append(sv)\n        if zm:\n            if zm not in by_zoom:\n                by_zoom[zm] = {\"pan\": {}, \"tilt\": {}}\n            if ax in (\"pan\", \"tilt\") and sl:\n                by_zoom[zm][ax][sl] = round(sv, 2)\n    # Average\n    for k in speed_map:\n        speed_map[k] = round(sum(speed_map[k]) / len(speed_map[k]), 2)\n    for k in pan_map:\n        pan_map[k] = round(sum(pan_map[k]) / len(pan_map[k]), 2)\n    for k in tilt_map:\n        tilt_map[k] = round(sum(tilt_map[k]) / len(tilt_map[k]), 2)\n    results = {\n        \"speed_map\": speed_map,\n        \"pan_speed\": pan_map,\n        \"tilt_speed\": tilt_map,\n        \"by_zoom\": by_zoom,\n        \"total_tests\": len(results),\n        \"success\": len(results) > 0,\n    }\n```\n\nSo I need to apply this same processing in the detect flow. Let me find the exact lines.\n\nLooking at the detect flow code:\n```python\nspeed_result = await asyncio.to_thread(speed_tester.run_all_tests, None, req.speed_profile, speed_progress_callback)\nif not speed_result:\n    detect_tasks[task_id].update(status=\"failed\", current_step=\"speed: 无结果\")\n    return\nresults[\"speed\"] = speed_result\n```\n\nI need to process `speed_result` here. Let me also check the `renderAdvResult` function to see if it needs to handle the nested `{\"speed\": ...}` structure or if I should process at the backend.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach: process `speed_result` in the detect flow to match the format that `renderAdvResult` expects. The `renderAdvResult` checks `results.speed_map` and `results.pan_speed` at the top level. So I should store the processed dict as `results[\"speed\"]`.\n\nBut wait - `results` in the detect flow is `{\"speed\": speed_result}`, and then the detect result endpoint returns `{\"success\": True, \"results\": {\"speed\": speed_result}}`. Then `renderAdvResult` gets `data.results` = `{\"speed\": speed_result}`.\n\nSo `results` in `renderAdvResult` = `{\"speed\": processed_dict}`. And it checks `results.speed_map` - which would be undefined because `speed_map` is inside `results.speed`.\n\nSo there are two approaches:\n1. Process in backend AND fix `renderAdvResult` to unwrap\n2. Just fix `renderAdvResult` to handle the nested structure\n\nApproach 1 is cleaner. Let me:\n1. In router.py detect flow: process `speed_result` list into dict format\n2. In advanced.html `renderAdvResult`: handle the nested `results.speed` structure\n\nActually, the simplest fix that touches the least code: in `renderAdvResult`, when results has a `speed` key, use `results.speed` instead of `results` for the speed check.\n\nBut that still won't work because `results.speed` is a raw list, not a processed dict.\n\nSo I need to do both:\n1. Process `speed_result` in the detect flow (router.py)\n2. Fix `renderAdvResult` to unwrap `results.speed` (advanced.html)\n\nOR: just process in the detect flow and store at the top level:\n```python\n# Instead of: results[\"speed\"] = speed_result\n# Do: results.update(processed_speed_dict)\n```\n\nThis way `results` would have `speed_map`, `pan_speed`, etc. at the top level, and `renderAdvResult` would work without changes.\n\nBut that might break other things that expect `results[\"speed\"]` to exist. Let me check...\n\nActually, looking at the detect result endpoint, it returns `task.get(\"results\", {})`. And the frontend calls `renderAdvResult(data)` where `data.results` is this dict. So if I store speed data at the top level of `results`, it would work.\n\nBut wait, the detect flow stores multiple test results: `results[\"function\"]`, `results[\"limit\"]`, `results[\"speed\"]`. If I flatten speed into top-level, it would mix with function and limit keys.\n\nThe cleanest approach: process `speed_result` in the detect flow AND fix `renderAdvResult` to handle `results.speed`:\n\n```javascript\n// In renderAdvResult, before the speed check:\nconst speedData = results.speed || results;\nif (speedData.speed_map !== undefined || speedData.pan_speed !== undefined) {\n    // use speedData instead of results\n}\n```\n\nLet me implement this. First, process in router.py detect flow, then fix advanced.html.\n\nLet me also check the `advanced_speed_run` endpoint to make sure I copy the processing correctly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"找到根因了。两条路径：\n\n```\n主控台: speedTestRun() → /advanced/speed/run → 返回 {speed_map, pan_speed, ...}  ✅\n高级测试: runAdvTest() → /advanced/detect/start → run_all_tests() → 返回 list ❌\n```\n\n`detect/start` 直接存 `run_all_tests` 的原始 list，没有做分组处理。`renderAdvResult` 拿到 `{speed: [list]}`，没有 `speed_map`/`pan_speed`，掉进 else 分支当功能测试渲染 → 显示\"项目 支持 范围\"。\n\n修复：后端处理 + 前端适配。\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_g1pc7bx11frkru9nkx9qbzbd","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"offset":2853,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":42355,"output":2799,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45154,"cost":{"input":0.042355,"output":0.008956800000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0513118}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782675126628,"responseId":"cht000f6482@dx19f0fb7bb13ba5d452"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e4637391","parentId":"cd83a03d","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:33:10.706Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_g1pc7bx11frkru9nkx9qbzbd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                    detect_tasks[task_id][\"last_result\"] = result\r\n                speed_result = await asyncio.to_thread(speed_tester.run_all_tests, None, req.speed_profile, speed_progress_callback)\r\n                if not speed_result:\r\n                    detect_tasks[task_id].update(status=\"failed\", current_step=\"speed: 无结果\")\r\n                    return\r\n                results[\"speed\"] = speed_result\r\n                detect_tasks[task_id].update(progress=95.0)\r\n                write_device_config(mac=_resolve_mac_from_ip(req.device_ip, ptz_mgr=mgr), speed=speed_result, ip=req.device_ip)\r\n\r\n            detect_tasks[task_id].update(\r\n                status=\"completed\",\r\n                progress=100.0,\r\n                current_step=\"completed\",\r\n                results=results,\r\n            )\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            detect_tasks[task_id].update(status=\"failed\", current_step=str(e), progress=0.0)\r\n\r\n    asyncio.create_task(_run_detect())\r\n\r\n\n[1197 more lines in file. Use offset=2873 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782675190706}}
{"type":"message","id":"ec877ded","parentId":"e4637391","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:33:20.374Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The root cause is clear:\n\n1. `advanced.html` speed test uses `/advanced/detect/start` which calls `speed_tester.run_all_tests()` and stores the raw list in `results[\"speed\"]`\n2. `run_all_tests()` returns a list of dicts, not a grouped dict\n3. `renderAdvResult` in `advanced.html` only checks for `speed_map`/`pan_speed` at top level, which doesn't exist\n4. So it falls into the else branch and renders as function test (项目/支持/范围 table)\n\nFix needed:\n- In `router.py`, the `_run_detect()` function: after `speed_result = await asyncio.to_thread(...)`, group the list into `{speed_map, pan_speed, tilt_speed, by_zoom}` before storing\n- Or alternatively, modify `renderAdvResult` in `advanced.html` to handle raw list\n\nAccording to the principle of doing grouping in backend (as we did for `/advanced/speed/run`), I should do the same grouping in the detect path. But the code is already duplicated - there's a grouping function needed.\n\nLet me check if there's already a helper function for this grouping, or if I need to add one. Let me look at the earlier fix in router.py.\n\nActually wait - let me re-read the earlier conversation. The summary says:\n- `router.py:2631-2645` — Fixed `results.get(\"success\")` and grouped list into `{speed_map, pan_speed, tilt_speed, by_zoom, total_tests}`\n\nBut the detect path at line ~2853 stores `speed_result` directly (which is the raw list from `run_all_tests`). I need to apply the same grouping here.\n\nThe cleanest approach: extract the grouping logic into a helper function, use it in both places.\n\nLet me look at what was done in the `/advanced/speed/run` handler:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_bkg0tQI6UMDGF0H8FaCE8531","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":50,"offset":2631,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":42901,"output":514,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43415,"cost":{"input":0.042900999999999995,"output":0.0016448,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.044545799999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782675190707,"responseId":"cht000d92ab@dx19f0fb8b49eb828262"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6cda0fb8","parentId":"ec877ded","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:33:20.385Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_bkg0tQI6UMDGF0H8FaCE8531","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        mac_clean = mac.replace(':', '').lower() if mac else \"unknown\"\r\n        config_saved = False\r\n        try:\r\n            store.save_speed_results(mac_clean, results)\r\n            config_saved = True\r\n        except Exception:\r\n            pass\r\n\r\n        # v7.118: 将list结果分组为前端所需格式 {speed_map, pan_speed, tilt_speed, by_zoom}\r\n        success = isinstance(results, list) and len(results) > 0\r\n        formatted = {}\r\n        if success:\r\n            by_zoom = {}\r\n            speed_map = {}\r\n            pan_map = {}\r\n            tilt_map = {}\r\n            for r in results:\r\n                sl = str(r.get(\"speed_level\", 0))\r\n                sv = r.get(\"speed_val\", 0.0)\r\n                axis = r.get(\"axis\", \"\")\r\n                zoom = r.get(\"zoom\", 0)\r\n                # speed_map: 所有zoom平均\r\n                speed_map.setdefault(sl, []).append(sv)\r\n                # pan_speed / tilt_speed\r\n                if axis == \"pan\":\r\n                    pan_map.setdefault(sl, []).append(sv)\r\n                elif axis == \"tilt\":\r\n                    tilt_map.setdefault(sl, []).append(sv)\r\n                # by_zoom\r\n                by_zoom.setdefault(zoom, {}).setdefault(axis, {})[sl] = sv\r\n            for m in (speed_map, pan_map, tilt_map):\r\n                for k, v in m.items():\r\n                    m[k] = round(sum(v) / len(v), 2)\r\n            formatted = {\r\n                \"speed_map\": speed_map,\r\n                \"pan_speed\": pan_map,\r\n                \"tilt_speed\": tilt_map,\r\n                \"by_zoom\": by_zoom,\r\n                \"total_tests\": len(results),\r\n            }\r\n\r\n        return {\r\n            \"success\": success,\r\n            \"message\": f\"速度测试完成: {req.device_ip}\",\r\n            \"results\": formatted,\r\n            \"config_saved\": config_saved,\r\n            \"mac\": mac,\r\n        }\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"速度测试异常: {e}\"}\r\n\n[1389 more lines in file. Use offset=2681 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782675200385}}
