{"type":"message","id":"7bace1e8","parentId":"7d9b79ca","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:35:12.851Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to fix the `fetchResult` function to handle speed results properly. The `progressEl` count update is also broken for speed (using `Object.keys(funcs).length` where `funcs = testResult.functions || testResult`). Let me fix both:\n\n1. `fetchResult`: Read `testResult = data.results[currentAdvTest] || data.results` - currently gets `{speed: speed_formatted}`, so `testResult` would be the full `data.results` with nested key. Wait, let me re-read.\n\nThe `_run_detect` function does:\n```\nresults[\"speed\"] = speed_formatted\ndetect_tasks[task_id].update(results=results)\n```\n\nSo `data.results` = `{\"function\": {...}, \"limit\": {...}, \"speed\": {...}}` and `data.results[currentAdvTest]` = the formatted speed dict.\n\nThen in `renderAdvResult(testResult)`:\n- `const results = data.functions || data.results || data;` → for speed, this would be `data.results` which is the speed dict.\n- Then it checks `results.pan_min !== undefined || results.tilt_min !== undefined` → no.\n- Then it checks `results.speed_map !== undefined || results.pan_speed !== undefined` → YES! This will render correctly now!\n\nSo the `renderAdvResult` should work if the backend sends the right format. Let me verify the flow:\n\n1. detect/start → creates task → runs speed → `results[\"speed\"] = _format_speed_results(speed_result)` ✅\n2. detect/result/{task_id} → returns `{\"success\": True, \"results\": {\"speed\": {...}}}` ✅  \n3. fetchResult → `testResult = data.results[currentAdvTest]` = the speed dict ✅\n4. renderAdvResult(testResult) → `const results = data.functions || data.results || data` → `data` is the speed dict itself → `data.results` is undefined → `data` is the speed dict\n\nWait, `renderAdvResult(data)` takes `data` as param. Then `const results = data.functions || data.results || data;`. For speed, `data` is the speed dict `{speed_map: ..., pan_speed: ..., ...}`. `data.functions` is undefined. `data.results` is undefined. So `results = data` = the speed dict. Then `results.speed_map !== undefined` → true! It renders correctly.\n\nBut there's still one issue in `fetchResult`: the progress count logic uses `testResult.functions || testResult` for all types, which for speed would give `{speed_map: ..., ...}` and `Object.keys(funcs).length` would count keys like `speed_map`, `pan_speed`, etc. That shows a wrong count.\n\nLet me fix the progress count in `fetchResult` too. Actually, let me also fix it to handle the count properly. The speed result has `total_tests` already.\n\nAlso, the main issue the user is seeing: they said the speed test completed but shows \"项目 支持 范围\" with numbers 0, 1, 2... - this is the `Object.entries(results)` that's rendering the speed_map keys (0, 1, 50, 100) as project names! Because `results.speed_map !== undefined` check was done, but wait... `speed_map` has keys like \"1\", \"50\", \"100\" etc. Let me re-check.\n\nActually wait. Let me re-read the original `renderAdvResult` flow before my changes:\n\n```js\nvar testResult = data.results[currentAdvTest] || data.results;\n// data.results = {speed: [list_of_dicts]}\n// testResult = [list_of_dicts]  ← this is a LIST\n// renderAdvResult([list_of_dicts])\n// results = data.functions || data.results || data → data is a list → results = list\n// results.pan_min → undefined\n// results.speed_map → undefined\n// falls into else → Object.entries(results) → iterates list: [0: {axis:\"pan\",...}, 1: {axis:\"tilt\",...}, ...]\n// key=0, val={axis:\"pan\",...} → val.label → undefined → 0\n// val.supported → undefined → 'N'\n// val.min → undefined → '-'\n// val.max → undefined → '-'\n// So displays: 0 N -~-, 1 N -~-, 2 N -~- ...\n```\n\nThat matches exactly what the user sees! The speed result is a list, and it falls into the \"功能测试\" else branch.\n\nNow with my fix on the backend side (making `results[\"speed\"] = _format_speed_results(speed_result)`), the frontend should render correctly without any frontend changes. But let me also fix the progress count in `fetchResult`.\n\nActually, I should also check the `renderAdvResult` function — let me think about whether it needs changes. The data will now be:\n```\ntestResult = {speed_map: {1: 0.23, ...}, pan_speed: {1: 0.23, ...}, tilt_speed: {1: 0.15, ...}, by_zoom: {...}, total_tests: 36}\n```\n\nThen in `renderAdvResult`:\n```js\nconst results = data.functions || data.results || data;\n// data.functions → undefined\n// data.results → undefined (data itself has no .results key... wait it does: results.speed_map.results? no, results is the dict)\n// data → {speed_map: ..., ...}\n// results = the speed dict\n// results.pan_min → undefined\n// results.speed_map !== undefined → TRUE\n// → renders speed table correctly\n```\n\nSo the `renderAdvResult` should work without changes. But the `fetchResult` progress count needs fixing. Let me fix that too.\n\nAlso, let me verify the syntax parses correctly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Now fix `advanced.html` 的 `fetchResult` — speed 时进度数用 `total_tests` 而非 keys 计数："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_DAheddVkVSXlYPyf29tt0923","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"        if (data.success && data.results) {\n            // v7.52: 从总结果中取当前测试类型的结果\n            var testResult = data.results[currentAdvTest] || data.results;\n            renderAdvResult(testResult);\n            // 更新进度显示完成数量\n            var progressEl = document.getElementById('advProgress');\n            if (progressEl) {\n                var count;\n                if (testResult && testResult.total_tests != null) {\n                    count = testResult.total_tests;\n                } else {\n                    var funcs = testResult.functions || testResult;\n                    count = typeof funcs === 'object' && funcs ? Object.keys(funcs).length : 0;\n                }\n                progressEl.textContent = currentAdvTest + ' 完成(' + count + ')';\n            }","oldText":"        if (data.success && data.results) {\n            // v7.52: 从总结果中取当前测试类型的结果\n            var testResult = data.results[currentAdvTest] || data.results;\n            renderAdvResult(testResult);\n            // 更新进度显示完成数量\n            var progressEl = document.getElementById('advProgress');\n            if (progressEl) {\n                var funcs = testResult.functions || testResult;\n                var count = Object.keys(funcs).length;\n                progressEl.textContent = currentAdvTest + ' 完成(' + count + ')';\n            }"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\includes\\advanced.html"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":49265,"output":1745,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51010,"cost":{"input":0.049264999999999996,"output":0.005584,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.054848999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782675294023,"responseId":"cht000d3ce3@dx19f0fba480fba5b432"}}
