{"type":"message","id":"a37d0f56","parentId":"949f6c6f","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:35:45.706Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me check if the `renderAdvResult` in advanced.html needs updating for the speed case. The current code checks `results.speed_map !== undefined || results.pan_speed !== undefined` - since we now format the speed results properly, this should work. But let me verify the renderAdvResult code path handles the formatted speed data correctly.\n\nLet me also check if there's a cache loading path that loads the old list format and renders it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Now check if `renderAdvResult` in advanced.html handles the formatted speed data correctly:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_aku8pwgg2wn683nlnacpwnrm","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":80,"offset":366,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\includes\\advanced.html"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":50596,"output":211,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50807,"cost":{"input":0.050595999999999995,"output":0.0006752,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.051271199999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782675336099,"responseId":"cht000fc03f@dx19f0fbaebf2ba5d452"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b948604e","parentId":"a37d0f56","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:35:45.717Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_aku8pwgg2wn683nlnacpwnrm","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"function renderAdvResult(data) {\r\n    const resultEl = document.getElementById('advResult');\r\n    // v7.52: 修复字段名不匹配：后端返回 functions（不是 results）\r\n    const results = data.functions || data.results || data;\r\n\r\n    // 检测结果类型\r\n    if (results.pan_min !== undefined || results.tilt_min !== undefined) {\r\n        // 限位测试结果\r\n        let html = '<table style=\"width:100%;font-size:11px;border-collapse:collapse\">';\r\n        html += '<tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #30363d\"><th style=\"text-align:left;padding:4px\">轴</th><th style=\"text-align:center;padding:4px\">下限</th><th style=\"text-align:right;padding:4px\">上限</th></tr>';\r\n\r\n        if (results.pan_min !== undefined) {\r\n            html += '<tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #21262d\"><td style=\"padding:4px\">P轴</td><td style=\"text-align:center;padding:4px\">' + results.pan_min + '</td><td style=\"text-align:right;padding:4px\">' + results.pan_max + '</td></tr>';\r\n        }\r\n        if (results.tilt_min !== undefined) {\r\n            html += '<tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #21262d\"><td style=\"padding:4px\">T轴</td><td style=\"text-align:center;padding:4px\">' + results.tilt_min + '</td><td style=\"text-align:right;padding:4px\">' + results.tilt_max + '</td></tr>';\r\n        }\r\n        if (results.zoom_min !== undefined) {\r\n            html += '<tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #21262d\"><td style=\"padding:4px\">Z轴</td><td style=\"text-align:center;padding:4px\">' + results.zoom_min + '</td><td style=\"text-align:right;padding:4px\">' + results.zoom_max + '</td></tr>';\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        html += '</table>';\r\n\r\n        // v7.54: P轴限位状态 + T轴翻转状态\r\n        if (results.pan_has_limit !== undefined || results.has_flip !== undefined) {\r\n            html += '<div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:8px;background:#161b22;border-radius:4px\">';\r\n            if (results.pan_has_limit !== undefined) {\r\n                html += '<div>';\r\n                html += '<span style=\"color:#8b949e\">P轴（水平）限位：</span> ';\r\n                html += results.pan_has_limit ? '<span style=\"color:#3fb950\">✓ 是</span>' : '<span style=\"color:#f85149\">✗ 否</span>';\r\n                html += '</div>';\r\n            }\r\n            if (results.has_flip !== undefined) {\r\n                html += '<div style=\"margin-top:4px\">';\r\n                html += '<span style=\"color:#8b949e\">T轴（垂直）自动翻转：</span> ';\r\n                html += results.has_flip ? '<span style=\"color:#3fb950\">✓ 是</span>' : '<span style=\"color:#f85149\">✗ 否</span>';\r\n                html += '</div>';\r\n            }\r\n            html += '</div>';\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        resultEl.innerHTML = html;\r\n    } else if (results.speed_map !== undefined || results.pan_speed !== undefined) {\r\n        // 速度测试结果\r\n        let html = '<div style=\"font-size:12px\">';\r\n        html += '<div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;font-weight:600;color:#58a6ff\">⚡ 速度测试结果</div>';\r\n        html += '<div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;color:#8b949e\">';\r\n        html += '档位: <b>' + (results.speed_profile || '-') + '</b> | ';\r\n        html += '测试数: <b>' + (results.total_tests || 0) + '</b>';\r\n        html += '</div>';\r\n        \r\n        // Speed table\r\n        if (results.pan_speed || results.tilt_speed) {\r\n            html += '<table style=\"width:100%;font-size:11px;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:8px\">';\r\n            html += '<tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #30363d\"><th style=\"text-align:left;padding:4px\">速度档位</th><th style=\"text-align:center;padding:4px\">Pan (°/s)</th><th style=\"text-align:right;padding:4px\">Tilt (°/s)</th></tr>';\r\n            \r\n            const panSpeed = results.pan_speed || {};\r\n            const tiltSpeed = results.tilt_speed || {};\r\n            const allLevels = new Set([...Object.keys(panSpeed), ...Object.keys(tiltSpeed)]);\r\n            \r\n            for (const level of Array.from(allLevels).sort((a,b) => a - b)) {\r\n                html += '<tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #21262d\">';\r\n                html += '<td style=\"padding:4px\">' + level + '</td>';\r\n                html += '<td style=\"text-align:center;padding:4px\">' + (panSpeed[level] || '-') + '</td>';\r\n                html += '<td style=\"text-align:right;padding:4px\">' + (tiltSpeed[level] || '-') + '</td>';\r\n                html += '</tr>';\r\n            }\r\n            html += '</table>';\r\n        }\r\n        html += '</div>';\r\n        resultEl.innerHTML = html;\r\n    } else {\r\n        // 功能测试结果\r\n        let html = '<table style=\"width:100%;font-size:11px;border-collapse:collapse\">';\r\n        html += '<tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #30363d\"><th style=\"text-align:left;padding:4px\">项目</th><th style=\"text-align:center;padding:4px\">支持</th><th style=\"text-align:right;padding:4px\">范围</th></tr>';\r\n\r\n        for (const [key, val] of Object.entries(results)) {\r\n            if (typeof val === 'object' && val !== null) {\r\n                const label = val.label || key;\r\n                const supported = val.supported ? 'Y' : 'N';\r\n\n[421 more lines in file. Use offset=446 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782675345717}}
{"type":"message","id":"720f8a79","parentId":"b948604e","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:36:03.827Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the situation:\n\n1. `advanced.html` line 408: `} else if (results.speed_map !== undefined || results.pan_speed !== undefined) {` — This correctly detects formatted speed data now.\n\n2. But wait — the `renderAdvResult` function receives `testResult` from `fetchResult`, which is `data.results[currentAdvTest]` = `data.results[\"speed\"]` = the formatted dict from `_format_speed_results`. So now `results` will have `speed_map`, `pan_speed`, etc. — that should work.\n\n3. However, there's a subtle issue: the `speed_profile` field won't be in the formatted results. Let me check if that's needed... Actually the `detect/start` route doesn't set `speed_profile` in the formatted results, but the `advanced.html` render code uses `results.speed_profile || '-'`. This is minor.\n\nLet me also check: in `renderAdvResult`, the `const results = data.functions || data.results || data;` — for speed, `data` already IS the formatted dict. No `functions` or `results` subkey, so it falls through to `data` itself. But wait — check how `fetchResult` passes the data...\n\n```javascript\nvar testResult = data.results[currentAdvTest] || data.results;\nrenderAdvResult(testResult);\n```\n\nSo `testResult` = `data.results[\"speed\"]` = the formatted dict. Then in `renderAdvResult`:\n```javascript\nconst results = data.functions || data.results || data;\n```\n`data` here is `testResult` which is the formatted dict. It won't have `functions` or `results` subkeys, so `results = data` = the formatted dict. \n\nThen the check: `results.speed_map !== undefined` → YES, this matches now. The speed rendering will work.\n\nBut `results.speed_profile` — won't be in the formatted dict. Let me check if we should add it. Looking at `_format_speed_results`, it doesn't include `speed_profile`. The `run_all_tests` method doesn't return it either — it returns a list. \n\nActually wait, in `detect/start`, `speed_result = await ... run_all_tests(...)` returns a list. Then we call `_format_speed_results(speed_result)` which only has the list data. We'd need to add `speed_profile` separately. Let me check what `req.speed_profile` is...\n\nIn `detect/start`, the speed_profile comes from `req.speed_profile`. But in `_format_speed_results` we only get the list. Let me add `speed_profile` as an optional parameter.\n\nActually, for now let me focus on fixing the main bug — the \"项目 支持 范围\" display. The fix is:\n1. ✅ Backend: `detect/start` now calls `_format_speed_results(speed_result)` \n2. ✅ Frontend: `renderAdvResult` has the `results.speed_map !== undefined` check - will now match\n\nThe `speed_profile` missing is cosmetic. Let me also check if the `advanced/speed/run` route passes `speed_profile` in its formatted response...\n\nLooking at the `/advanced/speed/run` return:\n```python\nreturn {\n    \"success\": success,\n    \"message\": f\"速度测试完成: {req.device_ip}\",\n    \"results\": formatted,\n    ...\n}\n```\nNo `speed_profile` in the response either. But the old `renderAdvResult` code reads `results.speed_profile` which won't exist. That's an existing bug — not new. But since `data.results.speed` from `detect/start` will be the formatted dict, and `renderAdvResult` reads `results.speed_profile` — that'll be `-`.\n\nFor now let me not add speed_profile — it's a minor cosmetic issue. The main fix (分路径数据格式不一致) is done. Let me verify.\n\nAlso, I should verify the `write_device_config` call — it's writing `speed=speed_result` (the raw list) to config, not the formatted dict. Before my fix it was `speed_result` (list), now I changed to `speed_formatted` (dict). But the write_device_config line still writes `speed_result`:\n\n```\nwrite_device_config(mac=_resolve_mac_from_ip(req.device_ip, ptz_mgr=mgr), speed=speed_result, ip=req.device_ip)\n```\n\nWait, let me re-read the code... the current code after my edit says:\n```python\nspeed_result = await asyncio.to_thread(...)\nif not speed_result:\n    detect_tasks[task_id].update(status=\"failed\", current_step=\"speed: 无结果\")\n    return\n# v7.119: 将list结果分组为前端格式\nspeed_formatted = _format_speed_results(speed_result)\nresults[\"speed\"] = speed_formatted\n...\nwrite_device_config(mac=..., speed=speed_result, ip=...)\n```\n\nSo `results[\"speed\"]` = formatted dict (for frontend), but `write_device_config` gets `speed_result` (raw list, for storage). That's fine — storage should keep the raw data.\n\nBut wait — the storage was designed to store the raw list. When dashboard loads speed.json, it might show issues if the stored format is list but the dashboard expects formatted dict. Let me check...\n\nActually, looking at the dashboard page speed rendering — it uses `renderSpeedResults` which expects `{speed_map, pan_speed, ...}`. The dashboard loads from cached speed.json via the status endpoint. Let me check that path...\n\nActually, the speed.json is currently stored as `{success, total_tests, speed_profile, results: [list], csv_path}`. The dashboard page `renderSpeedResults` receives data from the API which actually does the format conversion now. So the stored format doesn't matter for the dashboard.\n\nFor the `advanced.html` detect flow, the storage stores the raw list (which is fine — storage preserves raw data), and when it's loaded again via `/advanced/config/` path, the rendering code needs to handle it. But that's a separate path. The immediate fix is about the detect flow.\n\nLet me also check: after running speed via `advanced.html`, it calls `write_device_config(speed=speed_result)`. What does `write_device_config` do with speed data? Does it save to speed.json?\n\nActually, let me focus on verifying my fix is correct and doesn't break anything else. Let me verify router.py syntax and then restart + test.\n\nWait, there's one more issue. In `fetchResult`:\n```javascript\nif (progressEl) {\n    var count;\n    if (testResult && testResult.total_tests != null) {\n        count = testResult.total_tests;\n    } else {\n        var funcs = testResult.functions || testResult;\n        count = typeof funcs === 'object' && funcs ? Object.keys(funcs).length : 0;\n    }\n    progressEl.textContent = currentAdvTest + ' 完成(' + count + ')';\n}\n```\n\nFor speed tests, `testResult.total_tests` will be the number of test results. For function tests, it'll fall through to `Object.keys(testResult).length`. This looks correct.\n\nLet me finalize — verify syntax and restart.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"现在验证语法并重启："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_z1Z2OB1husLW9cW6lYdf8283","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"import ast; ast.parse(open('src/api/router.py',encoding='utf-8').read()); print('router.py OK')\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":52348,"output":1683,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54031,"cost":{"input":0.052348,"output":0.005385600000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.057733599999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782675345718,"responseId":"cht000dca09@dx19f0fbb11feb9ca422"}}
