{"type":"message","id":"712b155d","parentId":"e3886ee3","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:52:42.814Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The boss is calling me out. He's saying:\n\n1. The main console speed test button (`btnSpeedRun`) doesn't exist in HTML — the UI was cut\n2. But I kept `function speedTestRun()` in index.html, which calls `/advanced/speed/run` directly\n3. Then there's the advanced test page that calls `/advanced/detect/start`, which internally calls `run_all_tests()` too\n4. And I added `_format_speed_results()` to handle both paths\n5. Then modified two frontend rendering paths (index.html `renderSpeedResults` and advanced.html `renderAdvResult`)\n\nHe's saying: since the main console speed test button doesn't exist, why do we need the `/advanced/speed/run` endpoint at all? And why have two frontend rendering paths?\n\nLet me think about what actually exists and is used:\n\n**Active paths that users actually see:**\n1. Advanced test page → `/advanced/detect/start` → speed test runs inside this → `renderAdvResult()` renders it\n2. Connect device page → `connectSpeedTestRun()` → this calls `/advanced/speed/run` directly → `renderConnectSpeedResultMini()` + `renderConnectFullResults()`\n\n**Dead paths:**\n1. Main console `speedTestRun()` → calls `/advanced/speed/run` → `renderSpeedResults()` — BUT btnSpeedRun doesn't exist in HTML, so this function is never called from UI\n2. `renderSpeedResults()` — only called by `speedTestRun()`, which is dead\n\nSo the dead code is:\n- `speedTestRun()` function\n- `renderSpeedResults()` function  \n- `_renderSpeedTable()` function (only called by `renderSpeedResults`)\n- `_renderSpeedByZoom()` function (only called by `renderSpeedResults`)\n\nThe `/advanced/speed/run` endpoint IS still needed because `connectSpeedTestRun()` uses it.\n\nThe boss wants me to list a cleanup plan. Let me be precise:\n\n1. Check if `speedTestRun()` is actually called from anywhere (onclick, event listener, etc.)\n2. Check if `renderSpeedResults()` is called from anywhere else\n3. Identify all dead code to remove\n4. Keep the working paths intact\n\nLet me also check what `_renderSpeedTable` and `_renderSpeedByZoom` are used by beyond `renderSpeedResults`.\n\nFrom earlier reading:\n- `_renderSpeedTable` — called from `renderSpeedResults` and `renderConnectFullResults` (speed type)\n- `_renderSpeedByZoom` — called from `renderSpeedResults` and `renderConnectFullResults` (speed type)\n\nSo `_renderSpeedTable` and `_renderSpeedByZoom` are used by BOTH `renderSpeedResults` (dead) and `renderConnectFullResults` (alive).\n\nLet me formulate the cleanup plan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"不是复制，是历史遗留问题。我来梳理清楚。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_K29rT28hOG1D6bVUAMWG4496","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"\nhtml=open('src/web/index.html',encoding='utf-8').read()\n# Check if speedTestRun is ever called (onclick, etc.)\nimport re\ncalls = []\nfor m in re.finditer(r'speedTestRun', html):\n    # check if it's a call vs definition\n    ctx = html[max(0,m.start()-50):m.end()+50]\n    if 'function speedTestRun' not in ctx:\n        calls.append(ctx.replace(chr(10),' '))\nprint('=== speedTestRun references (excluding definition) ===')\nfor c in calls:\n    print(c[:150])\nprint(f'Total non-definition refs: {len(calls)}')\n\nprint()\n# Check renderSpeedResults references\nr_calls = []\nfor m in re.finditer(r'renderSpeedResults', html):\n    ctx = html[max(0,m.start()-20):m.end()+80]\n    if 'function renderSpeedResults' not in ctx:\n        r_calls.append(ctx.replace(chr(10),' '))\nfor c in r_calls:\n    print(c[:150])\nprint(f'renderSpeedResults non-def refs: {len(r_calls)}')\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":77024,"output":939,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77963,"cost":{"input":0.077024,"output":0.0030048