{"type":"message","id":"7647d97f","parentId":"ac3bc0e9","timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:59:23.142Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The audit results are very revealing. Let me analyze:\n\n1. **ALL speed/limit/function test buttons and result areas are JS-ONLY** - meaning they don't exist in the HTML body. The `index.html` has a single-file architecture where all HTML is likely generated dynamically via JavaScript. So `btnSpeedRun`, `speedResultArea`, etc. might be dynamically created.\n\n2. But `btnAdvRun`, `btnAdvStop`, `advResult`, `advProgress`, `advOutput` are in `advanced.html` which is an included file. They're \"MISSING\" because they're in a separate file.\n\n3. The audit script strips `<script>` blocks but these ids might be in `<script>` blocks that dynamically create DOM elements. Let me check.\n\nActually wait - the first audit said `[BODY]` for all of them, but the second audit (which strips script blocks) says `[JS-ONLY]`. This means these ids are only referenced in `<script>` blocks, not in the actual HTML markup. They could be:\n- Dynamically created via `document.createElement` or `innerHTML`\n- Or truly dead code\n\nLet me check if there's dynamic creation of these elements. The `advanced.html` includes `btnAdvRun` etc. in its HTML markup, but they're in a separate file loaded via Jinja2 includes.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the second audit: it says `btnAdvRun` is MISSING. But `advanced.html` definitely has `btnAdvRun`. The issue is that `advanced.html` is included via Jinja2 template includes, so the IDs are in a separate file.\n\nLet me check if the main `index.html` uses Jinja2 includes to pull in the other HTML files. If so, then the ids from those files would appear in the rendered page.\n\nLet me look at how index.html includes other files.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2g9nyrlwyabs92wylsfqhi2g","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"\nhtml=open('src/web/index.html',encoding='utf-8').read()\nimport re\n# check jinja2 includes\nfor m in re.finditer(r'\\{%\\s*include', html):\n    end = html.find('%}', m.start())\n    print(html[m.start():end+2])\n# check all page-* ids\nfor m in re.finditer(r'id=\\\"page-[^\\\"]+\\\"', html):\n    print(m.group())\n# check if these elements are dynamically created\nfor kw in ['btnSpeedRun', 'speedResultArea', 'btnLimitRun', 'limitResultArea', 'btnFuncRun', 'funcResultArea']:\n    # find createElement or innerHTML patterns near these\n    idx = html.find(kw)\n    if idx > 0:\n        # look 500 chars before for createElement/innerHTML\n        pre = html[max(0,idx-500):idx]\n        if 'createElement' in pre:\n            print(f'{kw}: dynamically created (createElement)')\n        elif 'innerHTML' in pre:\n            # find what element\n            id_match = re.search(r'getElementById\\([\\\"\\\\'']([^\\\"\\\\'']+)[\\\"\\\\'']', pre)\n            if id_match:\n                print(f'{kw}: innerHTML into #{id_match.group(1)}')\n            else:\n                print(f'{kw}: innerHTML (unknown target)')\n        else:\n            print(f'{kw}: referenced but no createElement/innerHTML nearby')\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":84990,"output":783,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85773,"cost":{"input":0.08499,"output":0.0025056,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.08749559999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782676743911,"responseId":"cht000ddf02@dx19f0fd0684bba5b432"}}
