{"type":"message","id":"5819a3d4","parentId":"22e08d92","timestamp":"2026-06-28T20:00:14.597Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize:\n\n1. `index.html` uses Jinja2 includes to load 6 HTML files: dashboard, devices, console, observation, advanced, replay\n2. The speed/limit/function test buttons (`btnSpeedRun`, `btnLimitRun`, `btnFuncRun`, `speedResultArea`, etc.) are NOT in any include file - they're ONLY referenced in JS code within `index.html`\n3. The advanced page buttons (`btnAdvRun`, `advResult`, `advProgress`) ARE in `advanced.html`\n4. All the `speedTestRun`, `limitTestRun`, `funcDetectRun` functions reference HTML elements that don't exist\n5. The `connectSpeedTestRun`, `connectFuncDetectRun` functions also reference elements that don't exist\n6. The `_renderSpeedTable` is called from multiple places including `renderSpeedResults` (dead), `renderConnectSpeedResultMini` (dead), and `renderConnectFullResults` (dead) and also from `renderAdvResult` in `advanced.html` (LIVE)\n\nWait, let me re-check. `_renderSpeedTable` is called in `advanced.html` too? Let me check...\n\nActually looking at the audit output more carefully:\n- `_renderSpeedTable` has 7 callers\n- `_renderSpeedByZoom` has 3 callers\n\nThe question is: are any of these callers LIVE? Let me check if `_renderSpeedTable` is called from `advanced.html`.\n\nLooking at the advanced.html code I read earlier, it has its own inline rendering logic, not using `_renderSpeedTable`. So all callers of `_renderSpeedTable` are in dead functions.\n\nWait, let me re-read the advanced.html renderAdvResult speed section:\n\n```javascript\n} else if (results.speed_map !== undefined || results.pan_speed !== undefined) {\n    // 速度测试结果\n    let html = '<div style=\"font-size:12px\">';\n    ...\n    if (results.pan_speed || results.tilt_speed) {\n        html += '<table ...>';\n        // inline table rendering, not using _renderSpeedTable\n    }\n}\n```\n\nYes, `advanced.html` has its own inline rendering. So `_renderSpeedTable` and `_renderSpeedByZoom` are both only called from dead functions.\n\nNow let me compile the full report.\n\nKey findings:\n1. **ALL main console test functions are dead** - `speedTestRun`, `limitTestRun`, `funcDetectRun` and their renderers reference HTML elements that don't exist\n2. **ALL connect-page test functions are dead** - `connectSpeedTestRun`, `connectFuncDetectRun` reference elements that don't exist\n3. **The only LIVE path** is `advanced.html` → `/advanced/detect/start` → `renderAdvResult`\n4. **`_renderSpeedTable` and `_renderSpeedByZoom` are dead** - only called from dead functions\n5. **`/advanced/speed/run` endpoint** is only called from dead `speedTestRun` and dead `connectSpeedTestRun` - can be deleted\n6. **`/advanced/limit/run` and `/advanced/function/run` endpoints** - need to check if called from anywhere LIVE\n7. **No hardcoded secrets** found (the \"admin\" username hits are just default values)\n8. **`_format_speed_results`** is used by `/advanced/detect/start` which IS live - must keep\n\nWait, I need to check if `/advanced/limit/run` and `/advanced/function/run` are called from anywhere. Let me check the advanced.html... Looking at the code I read earlier:\n\n```javascript\nconst apiMap = {\n    'function': '/api/v1/advanced/function/run',\n    'limit': '/api/v1/advanced/limit/run',\n    'speed': '/api/v1/advanced/speed/run',\n    'astrocal': '/api/v1/calibrate/start'\n};\n```\n\nBut then it actually uses `/api/v1/advanced/detect/start` for all tests! The `apiMap` is defined but the actual code uses `detectApiUrl = '/api/v1/advanced/detect/start'`. So `/advanced/function/run`, `/advanced/limit/run`, `/advanced/speed/run` are NOT called from advanced.html either.\n\nLet me also check if `limitTestRun` and `funcDetectRun` are called from anywhere in index.html...\n\nFrom the earlier search, `limitTestRun` and `funcDetectRun` are in the `_expose` array at line 2696, which means they're exposed to window. But since their buttons don't exist, they can never be called.\n\nOK, now I need to also check if `_renderSpeedTable` is called from `advanced.html` or just from `index.html` dead functions. Looking at the audit output - `_renderSpeedTable` has 7 callers. Let me check if any are in advanced.html...\n\nActually, the audit only checked `index.html`. Let me also check `advanced.html`.\n\nBut from reading the advanced.html code earlier, the speed rendering in `renderAdvResult` is inline - it doesn't call `_renderSpeedTable` or `_renderSpeedByZoom`. So those are only in `index.html` dead functions.\n\nNow let me also check if `/advanced/speed/run` is called from `advanced.html` or just from `index.html`. The audit showed:\n```\n/advanced/speed/run: router=True, index.html=True, advanced.html=True\n```\n\nWait, it said advanced.html=True. Let me check... The `apiMap` in advanced.html has it, but the actual code uses `detectApiUrl`. So it's defined but never actually used. Let me verify.\n\nActually, looking at the code again:\n```javascript\nconst apiMap = {\n    'function': '/api/v1/advanced/function/run',\n    'limit': '/api/v1/advanced/limit/run',\n    'speed': '/api/v1/advanced/speed/run',\n    'astrocal': '/api/v1/calibrate/start'\n};\n...\nconst apiUrl = apiMap[currentAdvTest];\n...\n// But then it overrides with detectApiUrl:\nvar detectApiUrl = '/api/v1/advanced/detect/start';\n...\nfetch(detectApiUrl, { ... })\n```\n\nSo the `apiMap` is defined but the actual fetch uses `detectApiUrl`. The `apiUrl` variable is set but never used! That's another dead code issue.\n\nLet me compile the full report now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"现在检查 `advanced.html` 中 `_renderSpeedTable` 和 API 端点的实际调用：\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_upnuh9ym4dvsayf8atek3za0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"\nadv=open