{"type":"message","id":"35a3d5c0","parentId":"b80098b3","timestamp":"2026-06-28T20:22:16.213Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says after the cleanup, tabs can't switch, quick connect button is broken, can't connect devices, and the version shows 7.112 instead of 7.120. Let me investigate what went wrong.\n\nThe main issue is likely that when I deleted the dead code block from index.html, I may have also deleted some critical code that was between the dead functions. Let me check what was in the deleted region more carefully.\n\nAlso, the version showing 7.112 is suspicious - maybe the version string wasn't updated, or maybe the old backup was loaded somehow.\n\nLet me investigate:\n1. Check what was actually deleted from index.html\n2. Check if critical code was accidentally removed\n3. Check the version string\n4. Check the advanced.html changes","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8i341fgl7vezzais1jp0fsei","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"\n# Check what's between the deleted region in the backup\nbak=open('backup_20260629_clean/index.html',encoding='utf-8').read()\n# Find the deleted region\nstart=bak.find('//  Function Detection (P4.1-P4.21)')\nline_start=bak.rfind(chr(10),0,start)+1\nend_marker=bak.find('//  预置点列表管理')\nline_end=bak.rfind(chr(10),0,end_marker)\ndeleted=bak[line_start:line_end]\n# Check for critical code patterns\ncritical=['page-','nav-btn','switchPage','showPage','connectDevice','quickConnect',\n          'apiGet','apiPost','window.api','addLog','showToast','connectedDevice',\n          'discoverDevices','refreshDevices','deviceSelect','advConnectDevice']\nfor kw in critical:\n    if kw in deleted:\n        # find context\n        idx=deleted.find(kw)\n        ctx=deleted[max(0,idx-50):idx+100].replace(chr(10),' ')\n        print(f'CRITICAL in deleted: {kw} -> ...{ctx}...')\nprint(