anced.html`? Let me check.\n\nActually I already verified: `_renderSpeedTable` is NOT in advanced.html. `advanced.html` has its own inline rendering.\n\nNow for the live functions between blocks:\n- `onConnectDeviceChange` - defined once, never called → DEAD\n- `connectFuncDetectRun` - dead (no connectFuncResultMini)\n- `renderConnectFuncResultMini` - dead (no connectFuncResultMini)\n- `connectSpeedTestRun` - dead (no connectSpeedProgress)\n- `renderConnectSpeedResultMini` - dead (no connectSpeedResultMini)\n\nThen LIVE functions:\n- `startDetection` - LIVE (used for device detection flow)\n- `runDetectionStep` - called by startDetection\n- `finishDetection` - called by startDetection\n- `addDetectionLog` - called by startDetection\n- `presetGoto` - LIVE (preset operations)\n- `presetSet` - LIVE (preset operations)\n- `renderConnectFullResults` - was called by connectSpeedTestRun/connectFuncDetectRun which are dead. BUT is it also called from somewhere else?\n\nLet me check renderConnectFullResults references.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"`onConnectDeviceChange` 也没被调用，同样死。现在精确计算每块的边界："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_NLEtzJHNcTmcJiKkAjNI5207","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"\nhtml=open('src/web/index.html',encoding='utf-8').read()\n# Check renderConnectFullResults refs\nimport re\nfor m in re.finditer(r'renderConnectFullResults', html):\n    if 'function renderConnectFullResults' not in html[max(0,m.start()-40):m.end()]:\n        line=html[:m.start()].count(chr(10))+1\n        ctx=html[max(0,m.start()-30):m.end()+80].replace(chr(10),' ')\n        print(f'L{line} REF: ...{ctx}...')\n# Also check _expose array\nidx=html.find('var _expose')\nexpose=html[idx:html.find('];',idx)+2]\nfor fn in ['renderConnectFullResults','startDetection','presetGoto','presetSet']:\n    print(f'{fn} in _expose: {fn in expose}')\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provide