{"type":"message","id":"3ae01f70","parentId":"9e5c40f0","timestamp":"2026-06-29T05:28:10.440Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_tk35wszilj47losu8dks02pr","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def _format_speed_results(results: list) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"将 run_all_tests 返回的 list 分组为前端格式。\r\n    \r\n    Returns: {speed_map, pan_speed, tilt_speed, by_zoom, total_tests}\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    by_zoom = {}\r\n    speed_map = {}\r\n    pan_map = {}\r\n    tilt_map = {}\r\n    for r in results:\r\n        sl = str(r.get(\"speed_level\", 0))\r\n        sv = r.get(\"speed_val\", 0.0)\r\n        axis = r.get(\"axis\", \"\")\r\n        zoom = r.get(\"zoom\", 0)\r\n        speed_map.setdefault(sl, []).append(sv)\r\n        if axis == \"pan\":\r\n            pan_map.setdefault(sl, []).append(sv)\r\n        elif axis == \"tilt\":\r\n            tilt_map.setdefault(sl, []).append(sv)\r\n        by_zoom.setdefault(zoom, {}).setdefault(axis, {})[sl] = sv\r\n    for m in (speed_map, pan_map, tilt_map):\r\n        for k, v in m.items():\r\n            m[k] = round(sum(v) / len(v), 2)\r\n    return {\r\n        \"speed_map\": speed_map,\r\n        \"pan_speed\": pan_map,\r\n        \"tilt_speed\": tilt_map,\r\n        \"by_zoom\": by_zoom,\r\n        \"total_tests\": len(results),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n@api_router.post(\"/advanced/detect/start\", summary=\"启动一键检测\", tags=[\"Advanced\"])\r\nasync def advanced_detect_start(req: AdvancedDetectStartRequest) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"启动异步一键检测 (Function + Limit + Speed)。\"\"\"\r\n    import asyncio\r\n    import uuid\r\n\r\n    task_id = str(uuid.uuid4())\r\n\n[1322 more lines in file. Use offset=2320 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782710890440}}
{"type":"message","id":"5ca69b83","parentId":"3ae01f70","timestamp":"2026-06-29T05:28:29.944Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `_format_speed_results` function builds `by_zoom` with `zoom` as the key. The issue is that `by_zoom.setdefault(zoom, {}).setdefault(axis, {})[sl] = sv` — for each result, it stores the last speed value for each (zoom, axis, speed_level) combination. But there could be multiple results with the same (zoom, axis, speed_level) — it only keeps the last one.\n\nWait, let me look more carefully. The issue might be that `by_zoom` returns empty because `zoom` is 0 for all results. Let me check what `speed_tester.run_all_tests` returns. Actually, the key problem is that `by_zoom` uses `zoom` (which might be the zoom position at test time) as the grouping key. But the frontend renders it as `_renderSpeedByZoom`.\n\nLet me look at how `_renderSpeedByZoom` works:\n\nActually wait - the issue described by the user is that speed test results don't show different zoom levels. Let me re-read the message:\n\n> 速度测试没有按照Z的位置区分\n\nThe speed test doesn't differentiate by zoom position. Let me look at the frontend rendering function `_renderSpeedByZoom`:\n\nI need to see what `_renderSpeedByZoom` does.\n\nAlso, I should check what data `speed_tester.run_all_tests` returns - does it include zoom position? If zoom is always 0, then `by_zoom` will only have one key `{0: ...}`.\n\nLet me look at the speed tester.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"...\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fb7jbm5ew5md5vvseili5la4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && Select-String -Path src/web/index.html -Pattern \"_renderSpeedByZoom\" -AllMatches | Select-Object LineNumber,Line"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"sf","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":62313,"output":431,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62744,"cost":{"input":0.06